YOUN HYUN-JAE

2
00:00:19,561 --> 00:00:21,479
SONG SEUNG-IL

3
00:00:21,563 --> 00:00:23,481
PARK HEE-SUN

4
00:00:23,565 --> 00:00:25,483
SHIN HYEON-WOO

5
00:00:25,567 --> 00:00:27,485
KIM GO-EUN

6
00:00:27,569 --> 00:00:29,487
KIM JAE-JIN

7
00:00:29,571 --> 00:00:31,489
HAM YE-JIN

8
00:00:31,573 --> 00:00:33,491
WOO SUNG-MIN

9
00:00:33,575 --> 00:00:35,493
KIM MIN-GEE

10
00:00:35,577 --> 00:00:37,495
LIM SU-BEEN

11
00:00:37,579 --> 00:00:39,497
LEE SUNG-HUN

12
00:00:39,581 --> 00:00:41,499
LEE JOO-YOUNG

13
00:00:41,583 --> 00:00:43,501
CHOI MINA SUE

14
00:00:43,585 --> 00:00:45,503
LEE HA-EUN

15
00:00:45,587 --> 00:00:47,505
JO I-GEON

16
00:00:52,385 --> 00:00:54,929
SINGLE'S INFERNO

17
00:00:55,722 --> 00:00:56,556
Go-eun!

18
00:00:59,517 --> 00:01:00,977
Oh. Yeah?

19
00:01:03,563 --> 00:01:05,315
When are you gonna hang out with me?

20
00:01:06,691 --> 00:01:08,777
I'll be down later, okay?

21
00:01:14,199 --> 00:01:15,617
The three of us could hang.

22
00:01:15,700 --> 00:01:18,787
Let's hang out later.
We'll be down later after our chat.

23
00:01:18,870 --> 00:01:19,746
All right.

24
00:01:26,503 --> 00:01:29,422
He can't seem to say to her,
"Can the two of us go somewhere to talk?"

25
00:01:29,506 --> 00:01:30,507
I-geon can't?

26
00:01:30,590 --> 00:01:32,967
It's because he knows
Sung-min won't let her go.

27
00:01:33,051 --> 00:01:35,678
- You think?
- Yeah, it's kind of awkward for him.

28
00:01:36,596 --> 00:01:37,597
Think he's blunt?

29
00:01:38,264 --> 00:01:41,142
What's going on with you, Mina?
What's the situation?

30
00:01:41,226 --> 00:01:45,063
Well, as of today, I think
I've finally settled on just one person.

31
00:01:45,146 --> 00:01:47,440
- My first choice.
- After going back and forth?

32
00:01:48,024 --> 00:01:50,527
- After a lot of back and forth, I--
- You were indecisive?

33
00:01:50,610 --> 00:01:51,820
Yeah, I was before.

34
00:01:51,903 --> 00:01:53,404
You must be relieved.

35
00:01:53,488 --> 00:01:54,989
But he's gone to Paradise.

36
00:01:55,532 --> 00:01:57,367
- Of course.
- I know.

37
00:01:57,867 --> 00:02:00,453
- Ah, today--
- I'm off to find my love.

38
00:02:00,537 --> 00:02:01,621
Wait. Why?

39
00:02:01,704 --> 00:02:04,582
- Go-eun again? Okay.
- Yeah, I'm off to see Go-eun.

40
00:02:04,666 --> 00:02:07,377
I suddenly thought to myself,
"What am I doing here?"

41
00:02:07,460 --> 00:02:09,963
- You have to fight for love. Go.
- Yes, I'll go and fight for it.

42
00:02:10,046 --> 00:02:11,714
- All right.
- He's going off to fight for it.

43
00:02:12,298 --> 00:02:13,800
I don't feel that bad about it.

44
00:02:13,883 --> 00:02:16,052
Sometimes you have to say those things.

45
00:02:16,136 --> 00:02:17,637
They're just so competitive.

46
00:02:17,720 --> 00:02:20,140
- Are they really?
- Seriously.

47
00:02:21,766 --> 00:02:24,894
They've been talking for a long time.
It's gotten dark outside.

48
00:02:24,978 --> 00:02:28,898
- Sung-min's such a chatterbox.
- But I think that's part of his appeal.

49
00:02:28,982 --> 00:02:32,485
You know how some couples talk
on the phone for three hours each time?

50
00:02:32,569 --> 00:02:35,321
He must be accommodating
when it comes to that kind of thing.

51
00:02:35,405 --> 00:02:36,531
Mmm.

52
00:02:39,826 --> 00:02:40,660
I…

53
00:02:40,743 --> 00:02:43,454
What are you two talking about
that's taking so long?

54
00:02:43,538 --> 00:02:45,748
- Us?
- Are you ever gonna stop?

55
00:02:45,832 --> 00:02:48,126
Shall we go in since it's cold?

56
00:02:48,209 --> 00:02:49,836
- Okay.
- Yeah, it's cold.

57
00:02:51,087 --> 00:02:53,506
Where's "in"?
Let's go to the dining area then.

58
00:02:53,590 --> 00:02:55,091
- Okay.
- Yeah.

59
00:02:55,967 --> 00:02:57,302
- Here.
- Thanks.

60
00:02:58,094 --> 00:03:00,263
Those two just won't leave her alone.

61
00:03:00,346 --> 00:03:01,389
Sung-min won't leave.

62
00:03:01,472 --> 00:03:03,433
There's no "I'll let you two talk"
or anything.

63
00:03:03,516 --> 00:03:04,934
You'd think he'd give them privacy.

64
00:03:05,018 --> 00:03:06,936
- He's talked to her for a long time.
- For two hours.

65
00:03:07,020 --> 00:03:08,438
He knows he can't leave them alone.

66
00:03:08,521 --> 00:03:10,231
- Should I sit in the middle?
- Yeah.

67
00:03:11,232 --> 00:03:12,442
Here, sit in the middle.

68
00:03:13,234 --> 00:03:14,736
- Sit in the middle.
- Okay.

69
00:03:15,403 --> 00:03:17,614
- I'll sit here.
- This is funny.

70
00:03:17,697 --> 00:03:19,991
What were you guys talking about
for so long out there?

71
00:03:20,074 --> 00:03:23,203
- You know, just this and that.
- You were talking forever.

72
00:03:23,286 --> 00:03:25,413
If we'd been left alone,
we would've talked till dawn.

73
00:03:25,496 --> 00:03:26,414
Oh.

74
00:03:28,166 --> 00:03:29,792
- Gosh.
- There you go.

75
00:03:32,879 --> 00:03:35,590
Oh, hang on.
Did you two go to Paradise together?

76
00:03:35,673 --> 00:03:37,383
- Once.
- Oh.

77
00:03:37,467 --> 00:03:39,302
Hmm. Right. So, who chose who?

78
00:03:39,886 --> 00:03:41,179
We chose each other.

79
00:03:41,262 --> 00:03:42,889
- You matched?
- We matched.

80
00:03:42,972 --> 00:03:45,225
- We paired up in a game.
- Yeah, we matched with each other.

81
00:03:45,308 --> 00:03:46,142
Mmm-hmm.

82
00:03:46,226 --> 00:03:49,437
We played a game together
and talked after then got matched up.

83
00:03:51,814 --> 00:03:53,107
That's what happened.

84
00:03:55,401 --> 00:03:56,236
Ah.

85
00:03:57,070 --> 00:03:59,322
I can't wait to see what happens tomorrow.

86
00:03:59,405 --> 00:04:00,615
Yeah, seriously.

87
00:04:01,616 --> 00:04:02,951
Yeah. Me too.

88
00:04:03,785 --> 00:04:05,161
They're all hanging out together?

89
00:04:07,997 --> 00:04:10,208
Look, they make such a funny picture.

90
00:04:10,291 --> 00:04:11,584
A literal love triangle.

91
00:04:22,470 --> 00:04:23,972
I wonder what we'll be doing.

92
00:04:26,140 --> 00:04:27,642
Sung-min's guarding his spot there

93
00:04:27,725 --> 00:04:30,353
despite doing nothing
but making small talk.

94
00:04:30,436 --> 00:04:32,647
- He's keeping watch.
- For sure.

95
00:04:33,606 --> 00:04:35,358
I wonder what we'll be doing.

96
00:04:41,531 --> 00:04:43,283
I might go get an ice cream.

97
00:04:45,451 --> 00:04:46,286
WATER FOUNTAIN

98
00:04:46,369 --> 00:04:49,038
- <i>There's ice cream?</i>
- <i>At the water station?</i>

99
00:04:51,749 --> 00:04:53,501
ONLY OPEN AFTER SUNSET
1 PER PERSON, NO DELIVERIES

100
00:04:53,584 --> 00:04:54,961
<i>One per person.</i>

101
00:04:56,671 --> 00:04:58,923
<i>The amenities have improved a lot.</i>

102
00:05:00,425 --> 00:05:02,719
Ice cream reminds me of college retreats.

103
00:05:05,305 --> 00:05:07,056
I might go get an ice cream.

104
00:05:07,890 --> 00:05:08,891
With who?

105
00:05:09,976 --> 00:05:12,312
- "With who?"
- The three of them together?

106
00:05:14,814 --> 00:05:18,443
This time I'll go with I-geon
and have a chat with him.

107
00:05:18,526 --> 00:05:20,778
I'll go with I-geon
and have a chat with him.

108
00:05:20,862 --> 00:05:22,196
Go and get ice cream.

109
00:05:22,280 --> 00:05:23,781
- See you later.
- Okay.

110
00:05:29,120 --> 00:05:31,581
What could you possibly
talk about for four hours?

111
00:05:31,664 --> 00:05:33,124
- Four hours?
- Yes.

112
00:05:33,207 --> 00:05:35,460
What are you talking about?
It wasn't four hours.

113
00:05:35,960 --> 00:05:38,963
I was trying to be patient
the whole time and not…

114
00:05:39,047 --> 00:05:40,673
- I was, uh… you know?
- You know?

115
00:05:40,757 --> 00:05:44,093
In the end,
I was forced to, like, be the third wheel.

116
00:05:44,761 --> 00:05:46,763
Did you say four hours?

117
00:05:46,846 --> 00:05:48,598
- Maybe not four hours.
- No.

118
00:05:50,475 --> 00:05:52,143
- Have you been there?
- Where?

119
00:05:52,226 --> 00:05:55,188
- There.
- Uh, yes, I have.

120
00:05:55,271 --> 00:05:56,356
Oh.

121
00:05:56,439 --> 00:05:58,358
There's basically nowhere
you haven't already been.

122
00:05:58,441 --> 00:06:00,443
Seriously.

123
00:06:01,819 --> 00:06:03,446
- Well…
- This is so annoying.

124
00:06:03,529 --> 00:06:06,991
There are loads of places
I haven't been to, <i>oppa.</i>

125
00:06:07,075 --> 00:06:08,076
Which way is it?

126
00:06:09,494 --> 00:06:11,829
- We keep going a little further.
- Okay.

127
00:06:13,623 --> 00:06:16,709
- All right, here's the spot.
- Yeah, I've been here once.

128
00:06:17,835 --> 00:06:19,212
- For water?
- Yeah.

129
00:06:19,295 --> 00:06:22,924
- There isn't anywhere you haven't been.
- Well, I have to get water.

130
00:06:26,010 --> 00:06:29,639
- So we can only come here after sunset?
- Yeah, it has to be totally dark.

131
00:06:31,182 --> 00:06:32,934
Oh, yum! I want Okdongja.

132
00:06:33,476 --> 00:06:36,396
Oh. It's melted a bit.
You should have it quickly.

133
00:06:37,855 --> 00:06:38,856
- Oh.
- Oh no.

134
00:06:44,529 --> 00:06:45,947
Oh, that looks really good.

135
00:06:47,573 --> 00:06:49,075
- It's tasty.
- Mmm.

136
00:06:55,248 --> 00:06:57,208
- What's wrong with me?
- Here. Get up.

137
00:06:57,291 --> 00:06:59,377
Just get up and launch it off. Yeah.

138
00:07:03,464 --> 00:07:05,466
Honestly, what's wrong with me?

139
00:07:05,550 --> 00:07:06,884
This always happens.

140
00:07:07,468 --> 00:07:09,095
- You always drop food?
- Mmm.

141
00:07:12,640 --> 00:07:15,726
I got it all over the table.
Should I rinse it off with water?

142
00:07:18,855 --> 00:07:21,065
Uh… I'll do it.

143
00:07:22,275 --> 00:07:23,443
Get up for a sec.

144
00:07:31,409 --> 00:07:33,327
What was that?

145
00:07:33,411 --> 00:07:35,204
Ah…

146
00:07:48,050 --> 00:07:50,011
I can't help but laugh with them.

147
00:07:50,094 --> 00:07:53,598
It's because we're following
the emotional arc of these two.

148
00:07:53,681 --> 00:07:56,392
- Such a small thing but so funny.
- I know.

149
00:07:57,018 --> 00:07:59,770
Oh no. I totally missed, didn't I?

150
00:07:59,854 --> 00:08:01,981
Seriously, <i>oppa, </i>you com…

151
00:08:04,108 --> 00:08:05,568
This is nerve-racking.

152
00:08:05,651 --> 00:08:07,612
- You completely missed.
- Just wait.

153
00:08:10,239 --> 00:08:11,324
This is so funny.

154
00:08:13,868 --> 00:08:15,286
It's so funny.

155
00:08:15,369 --> 00:08:17,121
Oh shit.

156
00:08:17,872 --> 00:08:18,956
- Watch me.
- Okay.

157
00:08:23,544 --> 00:08:24,462
I got it?

158
00:08:25,379 --> 00:08:26,881
Oh, nice, nice.

159
00:08:33,346 --> 00:08:37,099
I am curious
what you're like as a boyfriend.

160
00:08:39,310 --> 00:08:40,394
- Me?
- Yeah.

161
00:08:45,024 --> 00:08:47,360
How about you? As a girlfriend?

162
00:08:48,152 --> 00:08:51,781
I really hate it when they repeatedly
do something I dislike.

163
00:08:52,573 --> 00:08:53,658
Such as?

164
00:08:54,909 --> 00:08:58,287
- I hate being addressed as "hey" or "you."
- Oh, "hey" or "you."

165
00:08:58,371 --> 00:09:01,999
That's why you asked me
that question in Paradise.

166
00:09:02,083 --> 00:09:03,292
Mmm. Mmm, that's right.

167
00:09:03,960 --> 00:09:04,794
DAY 4 PARADISE

168
00:09:04,877 --> 00:09:07,713
Since I don't know the guys yet,
I'm not sure what to ask.

169
00:09:07,797 --> 00:09:09,298
Yeah. Joo-young?

170
00:09:10,675 --> 00:09:12,927
Is there anyone
you're most attracted to right now?

171
00:09:13,511 --> 00:09:14,345
There is.

172
00:09:14,428 --> 00:09:15,805
- There is?
- Mmm.

173
00:09:16,514 --> 00:09:18,933
Watch and see if you can guess.

174
00:09:20,476 --> 00:09:23,145
Like, "Hey, it's him, right?"

175
00:09:24,939 --> 00:09:27,149
Do you say "hey"
when calling your girlfriend?

176
00:09:27,233 --> 00:09:28,526
Huh? My girlfriend?

177
00:09:29,110 --> 00:09:31,195
- No, of course not.
- Mmm.

178
00:09:32,989 --> 00:09:35,908
- No, really, I don't say "hey."
- Mmm.

179
00:09:39,328 --> 00:09:41,539
Who addresses their girlfriend
with "hey" or "you"?

180
00:09:41,622 --> 00:09:44,542
Exactly. Even if we're fighting,
if someone calls me that--

181
00:09:44,625 --> 00:09:46,711
- When they're angry? Yeah, I see.
- I'm…

182
00:09:46,794 --> 00:09:49,630
I have a feeling you'd say that
when you're fighting.

183
00:09:52,425 --> 00:09:54,260
- If I'm being honest…
- Yeah.

184
00:09:54,343 --> 00:09:57,179
Let me think for a second.
When I was fighting…

185
00:09:58,180 --> 00:09:59,807
My memory might be a bit distorted,

186
00:09:59,890 --> 00:10:03,227
but I don't remember
addressing a girlfriend with "hey."

187
00:10:03,311 --> 00:10:06,397
- I think I've called them "you," though.
- "You" is kind of…

188
00:10:06,981 --> 00:10:09,567
"You did this, you said this,"
I may have said that.

189
00:10:10,318 --> 00:10:11,736
That's not bad, I guess.

190
00:10:20,995 --> 00:10:22,204
That's not so bad.

191
00:10:23,039 --> 00:10:24,957
And you, when you're fighting?

192
00:10:25,833 --> 00:10:27,043
When fighting?

193
00:10:27,126 --> 00:10:29,629
- Well, you--
- I kinda want to see you get angry.

194
00:10:29,712 --> 00:10:31,839
I don't think
I bring things up right away.

195
00:10:31,922 --> 00:10:33,341
- I keep it to myself.
- Why?

196
00:10:34,175 --> 00:10:37,178
Because I could be mistaken
or could've misunderstood something.

197
00:10:37,261 --> 00:10:38,929
- I know exactly what you mean.
- Yeah.

198
00:10:39,013 --> 00:10:41,057
Let's say I have
a particular thought at night.

199
00:10:41,140 --> 00:10:44,060
If I wake up the next day and have
that same thought, then I take action.

200
00:10:44,143 --> 00:10:46,479
Usually, I don't still have
that same thought.

201
00:10:46,562 --> 00:10:50,358
Exactly. You're not the same person
at night as you are during the day.

202
00:10:50,441 --> 00:10:51,400
That's right.

203
00:10:54,779 --> 00:10:56,322
Talking to you is really fun.

204
00:11:03,663 --> 00:11:05,956
Then you should've come down sooner.

205
00:11:06,040 --> 00:11:08,459
Don't you think?

206
00:11:11,045 --> 00:11:12,505
- I--
- Yeah, it's true.

207
00:11:18,427 --> 00:11:20,638
- This is the kind of energy.
- The energy is different.

208
00:11:20,721 --> 00:11:22,807
Yeah, it's totally different.

209
00:11:22,890 --> 00:11:25,726
- Seriously, you were so funny.
- How so?

210
00:11:26,227 --> 00:11:28,729
It was so funny when you threw the water.

211
00:11:29,563 --> 00:11:32,191
Seriously, that was a total miss.
That was…

212
00:11:32,274 --> 00:11:33,859
It was just--

213
00:11:33,943 --> 00:11:35,903
I was going to do it myself,

214
00:11:35,986 --> 00:11:37,196
but you insisted.

215
00:11:41,325 --> 00:11:44,078
So funny. You're a funny guy.

216
00:11:44,662 --> 00:11:47,081
And you're just super easy
to talk to as well.

217
00:11:48,165 --> 00:11:50,668
- I think so too.
- Oh, I see.

218
00:11:53,295 --> 00:11:54,797
When I hear them talk, it feels like

219
00:11:54,880 --> 00:11:57,675
they're having conversations
that further their connection,

220
00:11:57,758 --> 00:12:00,511
conversations with substance
that couples have.

221
00:12:00,594 --> 00:12:03,180
But I've never seen those
between her and Sung-min.

222
00:12:03,264 --> 00:12:05,975
There really must be something
about the first Paradise trip.

223
00:12:06,058 --> 00:12:07,560
- Like your first love?
- It feels like that.

224
00:12:07,643 --> 00:12:10,479
Both Mina Sue and Go-eun
have said the same thing.

225
00:12:10,563 --> 00:12:13,190
Because she went
on her first Paradise trip with him.

226
00:12:13,274 --> 00:12:16,277
Like, "Oh, maybe
Sung-min is special to me."

227
00:12:16,360 --> 00:12:17,570
Is that what she's thinking?

228
00:12:17,653 --> 00:12:20,406
Still, from where we're sitting,
I-geon seems to be her top choice.

229
00:12:20,489 --> 00:12:22,742
- That's how it looks to us, doesn't it?
- Yeah.

230
00:12:22,825 --> 00:12:25,327
But we really can't tell
if she feels that way herself.

231
00:12:25,411 --> 00:12:26,495
We don't.

232
00:12:26,579 --> 00:12:29,790
- Can we come in?
- Of course. Come in.

233
00:12:30,458 --> 00:12:31,709
Which is Sung-hun's spot?

234
00:12:32,418 --> 00:12:33,252
Sam?

235
00:12:33,335 --> 00:12:34,587
- That one.
- This one?

236
00:12:34,670 --> 00:12:36,630
All right. I saw him reading a book here.

237
00:12:36,714 --> 00:12:38,340
Ooh, I'm cold.

238
00:12:39,175 --> 00:12:41,927
What the heck?
Seriously, what are you doing?

239
00:12:42,011 --> 00:12:43,929
Ugh, seriously? What's wrong with you?

240
00:12:44,013 --> 00:12:45,222
Ah, that hurts.

241
00:12:45,973 --> 00:12:47,600
What's wrong with you?

242
00:12:48,768 --> 00:12:49,977
No.

243
00:12:56,734 --> 00:12:59,570
This is what he reads?
He must be out of his mind.

244
00:12:59,653 --> 00:13:02,406
<i>Option Volatility and Pricing?</i>

245
00:13:02,490 --> 00:13:03,657
What the…

246
00:13:04,325 --> 00:13:06,744
- What are you doing?
- I'm so curious about him.

247
00:13:06,827 --> 00:13:11,081
I want to know everything right now,
but Hee-sun's going to find out first.

248
00:13:11,165 --> 00:13:13,959
It's all right. You'll get your chance.

249
00:13:14,543 --> 00:13:17,880
Ugh, why today?
I had to lose today of all days.

250
00:13:17,963 --> 00:13:20,299
Why couldn't I have come in third?

251
00:13:20,382 --> 00:13:21,759
Oh, actually, not third.

252
00:13:21,842 --> 00:13:24,470
I would've had to come in second
to get a chance.

253
00:13:25,262 --> 00:13:27,765
Well, if you get a chance
to go another time…

254
00:13:27,848 --> 00:13:30,184
But there was significance
to being the first.

255
00:13:30,267 --> 00:13:33,020
- You wanted to be the first.
- Yeah, I just…

256
00:13:33,771 --> 00:13:36,982
I so badly wanted
his first Paradise trip to be with me.

257
00:13:37,066 --> 00:13:39,735
- Mmm-hmm.
- But Hee-sun will get to know him

258
00:13:39,819 --> 00:13:41,028
during their time together.

259
00:13:41,111 --> 00:13:43,614
So when she gets back,
she'll know things I don't.

260
00:13:44,824 --> 00:13:48,577
She'll know them before me.
That gets to me.

261
00:13:48,661 --> 00:13:51,997
But didn't you feel Sung-hun's feelings
for you were pretty firm?

262
00:13:52,081 --> 00:13:55,209
That's what he said.
But what if he's not telling the truth?

263
00:13:55,292 --> 00:13:58,712
Well, Samuel has a unique kind of…

264
00:13:58,796 --> 00:14:00,548
- Standard?
- …determination.

265
00:14:00,631 --> 00:14:03,843
Everyone's telling you
that you have nothing to worry about.

266
00:14:03,926 --> 00:14:05,761
Just have some faith in him.

267
00:14:09,139 --> 00:14:11,267
Why does our girl Mina Sue always do this?

268
00:14:11,350 --> 00:14:13,936
She has no interest in them
when they're by her side

269
00:14:14,019 --> 00:14:15,563
and then pines for them when they're gone.

270
00:14:16,272 --> 00:14:18,315
- It's such a shame.
- Such a shame.

271
00:14:18,399 --> 00:14:20,067
What good does it do
to be moping on his bed?

272
00:14:20,150 --> 00:14:21,777
He's in a different bed right now.

273
00:14:21,861 --> 00:14:23,445
In Paradise.

274
00:14:23,529 --> 00:14:25,573
- That sounds very provocative.
- Word.

275
00:14:26,699 --> 00:14:28,033
I think she's one of those people

276
00:14:28,117 --> 00:14:30,786
that only realize
what they're missing once it's gone.

277
00:14:32,204 --> 00:14:33,455
PARADISE
PARK HEE-SUN & LEE SUNG-HUN

278
00:14:33,539 --> 00:14:35,374
- Let's go in.
- Let's get in.

279
00:14:36,083 --> 00:14:38,836
- Oh my god, that's so good.
- Isn't it warm?

280
00:14:38,919 --> 00:14:40,296
It's so warm!

281
00:14:41,589 --> 00:14:42,923
This is so nice.

282
00:14:53,100 --> 00:14:53,934
Mmm.

283
00:14:54,018 --> 00:14:55,519
- Good?
- Delicious.

284
00:14:56,770 --> 00:14:58,105
What's your love language?

285
00:15:00,566 --> 00:15:02,276
What makes you…
What do you like to receive?

286
00:15:02,359 --> 00:15:04,570
- I think I like being taken care of.
- Oh.

287
00:15:04,653 --> 00:15:06,989
Wow, okay, great.

288
00:15:07,072 --> 00:15:09,074
- Why "great"?
- I like taking care of people.

289
00:15:09,158 --> 00:15:10,826
- Oh, really?
- Acts of service.

290
00:15:10,910 --> 00:15:12,119
Oh.

291
00:15:12,995 --> 00:15:14,580
Why didn't you take care of me?

292
00:15:17,207 --> 00:15:18,042
In Inferno?

293
00:15:19,793 --> 00:15:22,004
How could I
when you were with someone else?

294
00:15:22,630 --> 00:15:24,882
- Mmm.
- No, I don't like to bother anything.

295
00:15:25,382 --> 00:15:28,218
Okay, so then,
which love language do you give?

296
00:15:28,969 --> 00:15:30,304
Do I give?

297
00:15:30,387 --> 00:15:33,182
- Well, I like giving gifts and--
- Gift giving?

298
00:15:33,265 --> 00:15:34,642
Ooh.

299
00:15:34,725 --> 00:15:36,185
That's kind of similar to me.

300
00:15:36,685 --> 00:15:40,022
And I also like taking trips together.

301
00:15:40,105 --> 00:15:42,024
- Oh, me too.
- Mmm.

302
00:15:42,107 --> 00:15:44,610
We're kind of compatible
in practical ways.

303
00:15:44,693 --> 00:15:45,527
Yeah.

304
00:15:45,611 --> 00:15:48,739
- I like vacations too, traveling together.
- Mmm.

305
00:15:50,366 --> 00:15:52,952
When you're dating,
do you see your boyfriend often?

306
00:15:53,535 --> 00:15:54,954
Mmm.

307
00:15:55,037 --> 00:15:58,666
I didn't get to very often 'cause I had
lots of long-distance relationships.

308
00:15:58,749 --> 00:16:01,794
I like seeing my girlfriend every day.

309
00:16:01,877 --> 00:16:03,963
Well, I guess New York's close.

310
00:16:05,339 --> 00:16:08,092
- Everything's close in New York.
- Yeah, that's true.

311
00:16:10,052 --> 00:16:12,805
Getting to know you better,
I'm still amazed.

312
00:16:12,888 --> 00:16:15,224
Like, what the hell?

313
00:16:15,307 --> 00:16:16,225
Seriously.

314
00:16:18,102 --> 00:16:21,146
I feel like we could be a good match
when we leave here.

315
00:16:21,230 --> 00:16:24,066
- Mmm.
- That's a big consideration for me.

316
00:16:24,149 --> 00:16:25,859
After we leave this place

317
00:16:25,943 --> 00:16:28,070
- and then go back to reality…
- Mmm.

318
00:16:28,153 --> 00:16:30,990
…who could I, realistically,
have a relationship with?

319
00:16:31,907 --> 00:16:34,660
I think, on paper, we're a good match.

320
00:16:37,371 --> 00:16:39,331
Just date then.

321
00:16:39,415 --> 00:16:41,750
- They are a good match.
- They suit each other.

322
00:16:42,292 --> 00:16:45,295
You know, now that we're on day seven,
this feels like my life.

323
00:16:45,379 --> 00:16:48,507
- Everyone's all in now.
- Exactly.

324
00:16:48,590 --> 00:16:52,094
Our life is get up in the morning
and immediately, "Let's talk."

325
00:16:52,177 --> 00:16:53,387
"Let's talk."

326
00:16:53,470 --> 00:16:55,139
We haven't had breakfast yet,
but let's talk.

327
00:16:55,222 --> 00:16:56,932
You never asked me to talk.

328
00:16:57,016 --> 00:16:59,852
No, I haven't really talked
that much to many people.

329
00:16:59,935 --> 00:17:02,146
Have you talked a lot
with Mina Sue, though?

330
00:17:03,272 --> 00:17:04,356
I think so.

331
00:17:04,982 --> 00:17:07,401
But she's honestly
kind of hard to figure out.

332
00:17:07,484 --> 00:17:09,069
Her feelings, I mean.

333
00:17:09,153 --> 00:17:11,905
- I'm sure she'll figure them out.
- Self-service.

334
00:17:12,531 --> 00:17:14,324
- Love is self-service.
- Mmm. Uh-huh.

335
00:17:14,408 --> 00:17:15,617
Love is self-service.

336
00:17:16,493 --> 00:17:18,704
- It's everyone for themselves.
- Exactly.

337
00:17:19,830 --> 00:17:24,668
From now on, though,
I told you, I will ask you more.

338
00:17:25,294 --> 00:17:28,130
- I'll talk to you tomorrow.
- Okay.

339
00:17:28,213 --> 00:17:29,423
And the next day too.

340
00:17:43,645 --> 00:17:45,814
- Things are changing.
- Yeah.

341
00:17:45,898 --> 00:17:47,900
This would work
because they're both in the States.

342
00:17:47,983 --> 00:17:49,902
- I think there's a real possibility.
- Yeah.

343
00:17:49,985 --> 00:17:52,821
- The vibe here was hot and heavy too.
- Mmm, right.

344
00:17:52,905 --> 00:17:55,324
- I mean, it could work logistically.
- That's right.

345
00:17:55,407 --> 00:17:57,785
They would be able to see each other
in the States.

346
00:17:57,868 --> 00:18:01,538
Sung-hun definitely has to go back there,
so that's a factor you can't ignore.

347
00:18:01,622 --> 00:18:03,999
Someone who ticks all the boxes
has suddenly appeared.

348
00:18:04,083 --> 00:18:04,958
Exactly.

349
00:18:05,042 --> 00:18:07,127
I also think it's not just
from Sung-hun's side.

350
00:18:07,211 --> 00:18:09,088
I think Hee-sun's
really flirting with him.

351
00:18:09,171 --> 00:18:11,048
Like, "Why did you never approach me?"

352
00:18:11,131 --> 00:18:13,050
I think Hee-sun's
really tempted right now.

353
00:18:13,133 --> 00:18:14,009
Yeah.

354
00:18:14,093 --> 00:18:15,719
They're good together.
They suit each other.

355
00:18:15,803 --> 00:18:20,057
But why does it have to be Sung-hun,
who's already connected to Mina Sue?

356
00:18:20,140 --> 00:18:24,311
If the odds are that Sung-hun
and Hee-sun will end up together,

357
00:18:24,394 --> 00:18:25,771
then there's a really high chance

358
00:18:25,854 --> 00:18:28,440
that Mina Sue will end up
with nothing at the end,

359
00:18:28,524 --> 00:18:32,444
apart from having gone through
this extreme arc of personal growth.

360
00:18:32,528 --> 00:18:36,365
Yeah, there's definitely something here.
Bad news for Mina Sue.

361
00:18:37,157 --> 00:18:38,700
PARADISE
LEE JOO-YOUNG & KIM JAE-JIN

362
00:18:38,784 --> 00:18:39,993
Here we are.

363
00:18:41,245 --> 00:18:42,746
I feel good after a shower.

364
00:18:44,581 --> 00:18:47,084
- Do you want to eat?
- Yeah. I'll probably eat.

365
00:18:47,167 --> 00:18:49,044
- Could you pour me a glass?
- Oh, sure.

366
00:18:51,046 --> 00:18:53,215
Today you'll have whatever you want.

367
00:18:54,341 --> 00:18:55,592
Anything you want.

368
00:18:55,676 --> 00:18:57,761
- Ah, that's the picture I wanted.
- This is it.

369
00:18:57,845 --> 00:18:59,138
- Yeah.
- This is the spot I wanted.

370
00:18:59,221 --> 00:19:00,472
Since you're the queen today,

371
00:19:00,556 --> 00:19:03,016
I'll wait on you like royalty
and bring you a fry.

372
00:19:03,100 --> 00:19:03,934
Okay.

373
00:19:04,643 --> 00:19:06,645
- And cheesecake, please.
- Of course.

374
00:19:10,983 --> 00:19:12,985
- A little cheesecake.
- Coming right up.

375
00:19:15,904 --> 00:19:16,822
Mmm.

376
00:19:20,159 --> 00:19:21,160
And what now?

377
00:19:22,661 --> 00:19:24,163
Cheesecake, please.

378
00:19:26,915 --> 00:19:28,709
- Remember, we can't leave any of it.
- True.

379
00:19:32,921 --> 00:19:35,883
I do think I'll miss the cheesecake
when I leave this place.

380
00:19:37,134 --> 00:19:39,219
- It's so good.
- Mmm.

381
00:19:44,808 --> 00:19:46,310
- Is this for me?
- Mmm.

382
00:19:54,234 --> 00:19:55,736
- Are you tired?
- Mmm.

383
00:19:55,819 --> 00:19:57,321
Your eyes look sleepy.

384
00:19:57,404 --> 00:19:58,322
Yeah, I am.

385
00:20:00,365 --> 00:20:01,366
Go brush your teeth.

386
00:20:01,450 --> 00:20:02,868
- With you as well?
- Mmm.

387
00:20:04,953 --> 00:20:05,871
Go ahead then.

388
00:20:08,790 --> 00:20:10,500
Can't you just brush them for me?

389
00:20:13,503 --> 00:20:14,338
Okay.

390
00:20:37,611 --> 00:20:39,571
Oh.

391
00:20:39,655 --> 00:20:40,948
What's with that look?

392
00:20:49,581 --> 00:20:50,999
Go brush your teeth.

393
00:20:51,083 --> 00:20:53,585
Should we change into our pajamas?

394
00:20:53,669 --> 00:20:54,962
Do you have pajamas?

395
00:20:56,922 --> 00:20:57,923
Isn't this so cute?

396
00:21:01,593 --> 00:21:02,678
Seriously.

397
00:21:04,763 --> 00:21:07,307
Once we're all ready for bed,
let's do face masks.

398
00:21:07,391 --> 00:21:08,725
Okay. But…

399
00:21:09,851 --> 00:21:12,729
If you're tired, go to bed.
I can't sleep 'cause I've slept too much.

400
00:21:12,813 --> 00:21:14,106
- Really?
- Yeah.

401
00:21:14,189 --> 00:21:16,441
- We'll be together tomorrow too anyway.
- Yeah.

402
00:21:31,999 --> 00:21:34,084
- Good night.
- Good night.

403
00:21:37,587 --> 00:21:40,966
I hate that I keep on smiling
like an idiot watching these couples.

404
00:21:41,049 --> 00:21:43,593
I was grinning too.

405
00:21:43,677 --> 00:21:46,388
- Yeah, you can't help it.
- I can feel it in the corners of my mouth.

406
00:21:46,471 --> 00:21:49,641
- I think it happens to all of us.
- But it just keeps happening.

407
00:21:49,725 --> 00:21:52,060
- Well, Jae-jin…
- I gotta close my mouth.

408
00:21:55,522 --> 00:21:59,192
PARADISE
KIM MIN-GEE & LIM SU-BEEN

409
00:22:00,569 --> 00:22:02,654
- Are those your pajamas?
- Yeah.

410
00:22:04,448 --> 00:22:05,574
These are my pajamas.

411
00:22:05,657 --> 00:22:08,076
- They suit you.
- Thank you. They were a gift.

412
00:22:15,083 --> 00:22:16,418
- Mmm…
- Shall we sleep together?

413
00:22:16,501 --> 00:22:19,379
- No.
- Oh, don't make me laugh.

414
00:22:19,463 --> 00:22:21,673
I know I said it, but don't make me laugh.

415
00:22:21,757 --> 00:22:24,593
- No, I promise you I was getting up.
- Mmm.

416
00:22:25,427 --> 00:22:27,721
Well, we can just talk
until we fall asleep.

417
00:22:27,804 --> 00:22:30,474
I like drifting off to sleep
while talking to someone.

418
00:22:32,559 --> 00:22:34,561
You must enjoy spending time with me.

419
00:22:35,354 --> 00:22:36,396
Yeah, I really do.

420
00:22:36,480 --> 00:22:38,607
- Mmm. I'm glad to hear that.
- Yeah.

421
00:22:38,690 --> 00:22:39,941
This is fun.

422
00:22:41,443 --> 00:22:44,946
If we get the chance, I would really like
to come here again with you.

423
00:22:45,822 --> 00:22:48,909
- Really?
- Well, this is the first time ever

424
00:22:48,992 --> 00:22:52,079
that I've clicked with a guy so well
right from the start,

425
00:22:52,162 --> 00:22:54,664
- and I don't want the conversation to end.
- Right.

426
00:22:54,748 --> 00:22:57,793
And I'm thinking,
"Oh no, we're running out of time. Ugh."

427
00:22:57,876 --> 00:23:00,295
Low-key panicking
but trying to play it cool.

428
00:23:00,796 --> 00:23:02,756
- Right.
- And I'm going, "Give us more time."

429
00:23:02,839 --> 00:23:04,591
"I wish we'd come here together earlier."

430
00:23:04,674 --> 00:23:06,593
Yeah, I do feel like
it's so late in the game.

431
00:23:06,676 --> 00:23:08,512
Yeah, we came really late.

432
00:23:09,137 --> 00:23:11,556
Now that we're here,
I find your face cute too.

433
00:23:11,640 --> 00:23:12,641
So strange.

434
00:23:13,517 --> 00:23:16,144
Seriously, how did we end up
coming here together?

435
00:23:17,312 --> 00:23:20,023
You don't just come here with someone
'cause you feel like it.

436
00:23:20,107 --> 00:23:20,982
Yeah, true.

437
00:23:21,066 --> 00:23:23,276
But we did end up here
because I felt like it.

438
00:23:28,657 --> 00:23:29,783
Are you laughing?

439
00:23:31,118 --> 00:23:34,037
- No, it's just…
- Yeah.

440
00:23:35,288 --> 00:23:36,665
Well, to be honest,

441
00:23:36,748 --> 00:23:40,585
compared to, uh, the first impression
that I had of you…

442
00:23:40,669 --> 00:23:41,503
Yeah?

443
00:23:42,087 --> 00:23:45,215
I don't know if I should say this,

444
00:23:45,298 --> 00:23:46,800
but you're kind of cute.

445
00:23:48,218 --> 00:23:49,970
Mmm.

446
00:23:50,554 --> 00:23:51,763
But I'm even cuter.

447
00:23:53,432 --> 00:23:55,350
I'm even cuter than I am now.

448
00:23:55,892 --> 00:23:58,270
I haven't actually shown you
my cute side yet.

449
00:23:58,353 --> 00:24:01,690
- Hmm.
- Yeah.

450
00:24:13,452 --> 00:24:15,829
- There's tension between them too.
- There is.

451
00:24:15,912 --> 00:24:18,748
You know, I've never seen
Min-gee like this before.

452
00:24:19,332 --> 00:24:22,544
Yeah, we got the impression
that she was unwavering,

453
00:24:22,627 --> 00:24:25,046
like a stick of bamboo
or a tree with deep roots.

454
00:24:25,130 --> 00:24:28,300
But at the end of the day,
Min-gee can be fickle like the rest of us.

455
00:24:28,383 --> 00:24:30,302
I think she really has been possessed

456
00:24:30,385 --> 00:24:32,554
since she had that conversation
with Mina Sue.

457
00:24:33,638 --> 00:24:35,432
The demon's gotten to her. For real.

458
00:24:35,515 --> 00:24:37,309
The demon's moving
from one person to another.

459
00:24:37,392 --> 00:24:39,686
- The demon's moved on to her.
- Like the two have been switched.

460
00:24:39,769 --> 00:24:42,772
This is nuts.

461
00:24:42,856 --> 00:24:46,276
Hey, yeah,
it's a totally logical theory, actually.

462
00:24:46,359 --> 00:24:49,362
The two of them are both suddenly
on completely different paths

463
00:24:49,446 --> 00:24:52,199
- from the ones they were on.
- I'm not used to seeing her like this.

464
00:24:52,282 --> 00:24:54,034
She's acting so cutesy all of a sudden.

465
00:24:59,789 --> 00:25:02,667
- Wake up.
- Did you get up early?

466
00:25:02,751 --> 00:25:04,669
Man, what a hangover.

467
00:25:04,753 --> 00:25:07,255
I definitely feel horrible
the day after I drink.

468
00:25:07,339 --> 00:25:08,632
My body feels so hot.

469
00:25:08,715 --> 00:25:10,258
She must've drunk a lot.

470
00:25:10,342 --> 00:25:12,761
- Enough for her to get a hangover.
- Yeah.

471
00:25:12,844 --> 00:25:15,347
Hmm. Hey, did we sleep together?

472
00:25:16,556 --> 00:25:19,768
- Your memory. Did you drink a lot?
- Yeah, I must have.

473
00:25:19,851 --> 00:25:21,269
How does he not know?

474
00:25:22,062 --> 00:25:23,605
Did… Did I sleep here?

475
00:25:23,688 --> 00:25:24,898
- Yeah.
- Oh.

476
00:25:26,566 --> 00:25:29,611
So… why did we sleep together?

477
00:25:29,694 --> 00:25:31,112
- Huh?
- Why did we sleep together?

478
00:25:31,196 --> 00:25:32,030
LAST NIGHT

479
00:25:32,113 --> 00:25:33,114
<i>He slept there.</i>

480
00:25:33,198 --> 00:25:35,075
<i>They must've slept in the same bed.</i>

481
00:25:37,410 --> 00:25:39,162
<i>Oh, he woke up. Oh.</i>

482
00:25:40,455 --> 00:25:42,040
<i>He must've just gone in.</i>

483
00:25:44,000 --> 00:25:46,002
Oh, I was just gonna sleep here, but…

484
00:25:48,672 --> 00:25:50,090
Oh, I'm so cold.

485
00:25:51,341 --> 00:25:53,552
- Min-gee, can I get in the bed?
- Hmm?

486
00:25:54,803 --> 00:25:55,637
Yeah.

487
00:25:56,304 --> 00:25:58,723
- <i>He was really sleepy.</i>
- <i>And cold.</i>

488
00:26:14,698 --> 00:26:16,449
<i>He genuinely just needs the comforter.</i>

489
00:26:16,533 --> 00:26:18,285
<i>Yeah, he's pulling the blanket out.</i>

490
00:26:19,244 --> 00:26:22,497
There's no ulterior motive here
on his part. He's just cold.

491
00:26:34,384 --> 00:26:35,760
Well, that was harmless.

492
00:26:35,844 --> 00:26:39,764
Sleeping together in this particular case
was purely due to being drunk and cold.

493
00:26:40,390 --> 00:26:42,601
- He needed the comforter.
- They just slept.

494
00:26:42,684 --> 00:26:44,436
Yeah, it was literally just to sleep.

495
00:26:44,519 --> 00:26:45,353
Yeah.

496
00:26:45,895 --> 00:26:47,981
Are you laughing?

497
00:26:50,734 --> 00:26:53,153
Oh, aren't you being
a bit too casual with me?

498
00:26:53,236 --> 00:26:55,155
- No.
- Wow.

499
00:26:58,033 --> 00:27:00,452
INFERNO

500
00:27:33,443 --> 00:27:35,779
- Is this the place you work out?
- Yeah, this is it.

501
00:27:36,363 --> 00:27:37,656
They're talking again.

502
00:27:38,156 --> 00:27:40,575
- That's so hardcore.
- Seriously?

503
00:27:40,659 --> 00:27:43,620
- Wow, seriously?
- He won't leave her alone.

504
00:27:44,287 --> 00:27:47,290
I mean, we know he's a chatterbox,
but this is just…

505
00:27:48,291 --> 00:27:49,292
Bright and early.

506
00:27:49,376 --> 00:27:51,002
- The crack of dawn.
- Jesus Christ.

507
00:27:51,670 --> 00:27:54,172
What's your workout going to be,
Mr. Paper Doll?

508
00:27:54,255 --> 00:27:56,466
- I do it all. I can lift that easy.
- Oh.

509
00:27:56,549 --> 00:27:58,593
Oh, really?

510
00:27:59,344 --> 00:28:01,429
- I can't imagine it.
- Seriously?

511
00:28:01,930 --> 00:28:03,264
I can totally bench-press that.

512
00:28:04,849 --> 00:28:06,476
I go hard when I work out.

513
00:28:06,559 --> 00:28:07,811
- You actually work out?
- Yeah.

514
00:28:17,821 --> 00:28:18,822
Is your face puffy?

515
00:28:19,322 --> 00:28:21,157
No. Why? Don't look at it.

516
00:28:21,908 --> 00:28:23,993
- Is it not?
- I think it is a little.

517
00:28:25,662 --> 00:28:27,539
Oh, it's definitely puffy.

518
00:28:29,207 --> 00:28:30,583
- What?
- It is a bit puffy.

519
00:28:30,667 --> 00:28:33,420
- Is it?
- Yeah. Your cheeks look kind of chubby.

520
00:28:33,503 --> 00:28:34,587
Oh no.

521
00:28:35,213 --> 00:28:37,841
I'm sure it'll go down if we keep walking.

522
00:28:43,054 --> 00:28:45,515
<i>I saw Go-eun and Sung-min</i>
<i>out walking together.</i>

523
00:28:46,224 --> 00:28:48,727
They even walked past me
while I was working out.

524
00:28:49,227 --> 00:28:50,353
I got so annoyed by it

525
00:28:50,437 --> 00:28:53,523
that I ended up completely overdoing it
with my workout today.

526
00:29:21,926 --> 00:29:25,930
I guess I'd probably be kind of annoyed
too if I were in his shoes.

527
00:29:26,014 --> 00:29:27,056
Of course it's annoying.

528
00:29:27,140 --> 00:29:29,517
I mean, couldn't they have
at least said hi?

529
00:29:29,601 --> 00:29:31,770
- I bet that was a workout booster.
- Yeah.

530
00:29:31,853 --> 00:29:34,564
- An all-natural workout boost.
- Yeah.

531
00:29:35,148 --> 00:29:36,274
The sun's not coming out yet.

532
00:29:36,357 --> 00:29:37,901
- So what do you think?
- About?

533
00:29:37,984 --> 00:29:40,069
About early morning in Inferno.

534
00:29:40,153 --> 00:29:40,987
It's nice.

535
00:29:41,070 --> 00:29:42,280
- Right?
- Yeah.

536
00:29:42,947 --> 00:29:43,782
Mmm.

537
00:29:43,865 --> 00:29:46,618
You know, your first
Paradise trip with Min-gee?

538
00:29:46,701 --> 00:29:48,119
How was it? Was it good?

539
00:29:48,953 --> 00:29:50,163
- You want to know?
- Yeah.

540
00:29:50,246 --> 00:29:54,000
According to Min-gee, she didn't feel
anything on that first Paradise trip.

541
00:29:54,542 --> 00:29:55,960
- Really?
- Yeah.

542
00:29:56,628 --> 00:29:58,213
But it was the same for me.

543
00:29:58,296 --> 00:30:00,882
I didn't feel any chemistry
between us either.

544
00:30:01,549 --> 00:30:04,886
But I definitely did feel it
when I went to Paradise with you.

545
00:30:04,969 --> 00:30:05,887
Be honest with me.

546
00:30:05,970 --> 00:30:08,223
What do you think you felt
when we went together,

547
00:30:08,306 --> 00:30:09,224
from your point of view?

548
00:30:09,307 --> 00:30:11,643
I always thought I was more of a listener.

549
00:30:11,726 --> 00:30:14,854
- Well, that's how it's always been for me.
- Oh.

550
00:30:14,938 --> 00:30:18,942
Yeah, but I found myself talking,
and I really liked that.

551
00:30:19,025 --> 00:30:21,528
I found I was talking about myself a lot.

552
00:30:21,611 --> 00:30:25,532
And I really enjoyed the experience.
It was so nice to be listened to for once.

553
00:30:25,615 --> 00:30:26,449
Mmm.

554
00:30:26,533 --> 00:30:29,160
Yeah, I really liked
being a chatty person.

555
00:30:29,744 --> 00:30:31,496
Yeah.

556
00:30:31,579 --> 00:30:33,957
My first impression of you was good too.

557
00:30:34,040 --> 00:30:36,584
But when I got to know you better,
I liked you even more.

558
00:30:36,668 --> 00:30:38,086
- Oh, I see.
- Yeah.

559
00:30:38,753 --> 00:30:41,297
So that's when I fully made up my mind.

560
00:30:41,381 --> 00:30:43,842
You've been my solid
number one choice since then.

561
00:30:43,925 --> 00:30:44,759
Mmm.

562
00:30:45,969 --> 00:30:48,429
You know, there must be
something between them

563
00:30:48,513 --> 00:30:50,014
that we are just not seeing.

564
00:30:50,098 --> 00:30:52,392
- When I watch them, yeah.
- Yeah, for sure. You're right.

565
00:30:52,475 --> 00:30:54,978
Maybe it's because
Sung-min speaks courteously?

566
00:30:55,061 --> 00:30:57,564
For example,
instead of addressing her as "you,"

567
00:30:57,647 --> 00:30:59,399
he'll address her as "Go-eun."

568
00:30:59,482 --> 00:31:02,193
That could be the kind of thing
she finds appealing in him.

569
00:31:02,819 --> 00:31:03,820
Well, let's guess.

570
00:31:03,903 --> 00:31:06,865
in terms of her feelings
for I-geon versus Sung-min,

571
00:31:06,948 --> 00:31:08,366
what would the split be?

572
00:31:09,200 --> 00:31:12,871
I think it's 80% I-geon and 20% Sung-min.

573
00:31:13,371 --> 00:31:15,164
- That's pretty uneven.
- Yeah.

574
00:31:15,248 --> 00:31:19,419
I'd say 60-40,
60 for Sung-min, 40 for I-geon.

575
00:31:19,502 --> 00:31:22,714
Only because if it were me,
I'd find it really hard

576
00:31:22,797 --> 00:31:25,300
to sit through those boring conversations
for such long periods.

577
00:31:25,383 --> 00:31:28,595
Because if you didn't like him,
being around him all the time

578
00:31:28,678 --> 00:31:32,432
and having those kinds of conversations
non-stop would be excruciating.

579
00:31:32,515 --> 00:31:35,101
The fact that she says she likes him
means she has feelings for him.

580
00:31:35,184 --> 00:31:37,312
They look like they talk five hours a day.

581
00:31:37,395 --> 00:31:38,229
For real.

582
00:31:38,313 --> 00:31:41,774
So, honestly, there's no way
she doesn't have genuine feelings for him.

583
00:31:41,858 --> 00:31:44,485
Rather than
a dopamine-fueled relationship,

584
00:31:44,569 --> 00:31:48,031
it could be that Go-eun prefers
a comfortable, uneventful relationship

585
00:31:48,114 --> 00:31:50,700
where, practically,
all they do is chitchat all the time.

586
00:31:50,783 --> 00:31:52,744
You might be right.
That could be the case.

587
00:31:54,203 --> 00:31:55,121
I don't know.

588
00:32:01,502 --> 00:32:04,130
Did you manage to do
everything you wanted to yesterday?

589
00:32:04,213 --> 00:32:06,549
- Yeah. Well, pretty much.
- That's good.

590
00:32:06,633 --> 00:32:09,552
- I want to go to Paradise again.
- Oh, yeah?

591
00:32:10,261 --> 00:32:12,764
Got it, got it. I'll do my best.

592
00:32:12,847 --> 00:32:14,223
- Yeah. Try your best.
- Okay.

593
00:32:16,601 --> 00:32:19,228
- They're here.
- No, you're lying.

594
00:32:19,312 --> 00:32:22,023
- That's a lie. Really?
- But there are only two couples.

595
00:32:22,106 --> 00:32:23,608
Oh, what's going on?

596
00:32:24,233 --> 00:32:26,152
- Joo-young and Jae-jin.
- They're behind them.

597
00:32:26,235 --> 00:32:27,236
Oh.

598
00:32:39,457 --> 00:32:43,753
Why sunglasses when there's no sun?

599
00:32:43,836 --> 00:32:45,838
Ah…

600
00:32:46,881 --> 00:32:48,216
Oh, Mina Sue.

601
00:32:48,716 --> 00:32:50,551
- Hello.
- You're back.

602
00:32:51,928 --> 00:32:53,262
- Welcome back.
- Hi.

603
00:32:53,346 --> 00:32:54,973
- We're back.
- Hello.

604
00:32:55,056 --> 00:32:59,060
Welcome back, welcome back.
Did you have a good time?

605
00:33:00,228 --> 00:33:02,563
- Hello
- Hi. Hello.

606
00:33:02,647 --> 00:33:03,856
- Hello.
- Hi.

607
00:33:13,282 --> 00:33:16,536
So, did you have a lot of good food?

608
00:33:16,619 --> 00:33:18,454
- Yeah, we did.
- Did you eat a lot?

609
00:33:19,789 --> 00:33:21,874
- What's this?
- You look pretty today.

610
00:33:21,958 --> 00:33:24,168
- Your shoes are so cute.
- They're cute.

611
00:33:24,252 --> 00:33:25,378
Oh wow.

612
00:33:34,929 --> 00:33:37,473
She's feeling awkward
'cause she enjoyed herself.

613
00:33:37,557 --> 00:33:40,351
- I know.
- You think that's how she's feeling?

614
00:33:40,435 --> 00:33:42,770
She can't approach--
Things are a bit awkward between them.

615
00:33:42,854 --> 00:33:44,897
- Yeah, that's why.
- Right.

616
00:33:45,648 --> 00:33:46,983
Did you have fun?

617
00:33:48,401 --> 00:33:50,319
I'm curious about Sung-hun.

618
00:33:50,403 --> 00:33:52,613
I wanna hear
how his first Paradise trip went.

619
00:33:53,698 --> 00:33:56,367
- I want to know his job and age.
- What do they do?

620
00:33:56,451 --> 00:33:58,286
Totally. Tell us, Hee-sun.

621
00:33:58,786 --> 00:34:00,413
Talking to him, I found…

622
00:34:01,664 --> 00:34:03,750
we have more in common than I thought.

623
00:34:04,500 --> 00:34:07,712
So now I feel more comfortable
with him than I did before.

624
00:34:09,797 --> 00:34:12,050
I think he's someone who understands me.

625
00:34:12,133 --> 00:34:14,761
- Like, he just gets where I'm coming from.
- Mmm.

626
00:34:14,844 --> 00:34:16,929
- That kind of…
- Mmm.

627
00:34:19,474 --> 00:34:23,394
I feel he's more comfortable and proactive
when it's one-on-one.

628
00:34:23,478 --> 00:34:25,688
In a group setting like this,
he holds back.

629
00:34:25,772 --> 00:34:27,940
- It's a challenge for him.
- He finds it difficult.

630
00:34:28,024 --> 00:34:30,651
- For Sung-hun.
- It can be difficult.

631
00:34:30,735 --> 00:34:33,237
- I think so too.
- Me too.

632
00:34:35,907 --> 00:34:37,825
I bet he's a really caring guy.

633
00:34:38,409 --> 00:34:40,119
- Like, sweet?
- Yeah, yeah.

634
00:34:40,203 --> 00:34:41,537
Yeah, he's so thoughtful.

635
00:34:41,621 --> 00:34:43,748
- I bet he's funny.
- He's so funny.

636
00:34:43,831 --> 00:34:44,957
He's hilarious.

637
00:34:45,041 --> 00:34:48,377
He's always like, "Oh, damn, damn."
It's always, "Damn."

638
00:34:48,461 --> 00:34:51,422
- "Damn."
- "Holy, holy."

639
00:34:51,506 --> 00:34:54,926
"Holy." His English is so good.
That's what makes it funny.

640
00:34:59,222 --> 00:35:01,516
- Oh, Mina Sue.
- This is hilarious.

641
00:35:01,599 --> 00:35:03,768
Not long ago,
Mina Sue would be the one talking,

642
00:35:03,851 --> 00:35:06,020
and Hee-sun would get anxious and stuff.

643
00:35:06,104 --> 00:35:07,647
- But now…
- The tables have turned.

644
00:35:07,730 --> 00:35:09,232
- …the tables have turned.
- Yeah.

645
00:35:09,941 --> 00:35:11,859
- How was it?
- I had fun too.

646
00:35:11,943 --> 00:35:14,403
- You need to be more specific.
- More specific?

647
00:35:15,446 --> 00:35:17,949
Honestly, it was so much more fun
than I thought it'd be.

648
00:35:18,533 --> 00:35:21,202
- Think you're compatible?
- Yeah, we are.

649
00:35:21,285 --> 00:35:23,371
As in, romantically?

650
00:35:23,454 --> 00:35:27,291
Well, first of all, our values
and dating styles are identical.

651
00:35:27,375 --> 00:35:30,378
Like, the way we think
is literally identical.

652
00:35:30,461 --> 00:35:32,713
- Really?
- It was like talking to a mirror.

653
00:35:32,797 --> 00:35:35,299
We were both like,
"Wait, you feel that way too?"

654
00:35:35,383 --> 00:35:37,802
And that was basically
how the conversation went.

655
00:35:38,469 --> 00:35:40,346
Like, "Wow, that's so weird."

656
00:35:40,429 --> 00:35:43,349
- So we had a lot of fun.
- You can't know until Paradise.

657
00:35:43,432 --> 00:35:45,351
Yeah, I think so. Mmm.

658
00:35:45,434 --> 00:35:48,813
But to be honest, I don't think
it would have been this great

659
00:35:48,896 --> 00:35:52,483
if I had gone with one of the other guys.

660
00:35:52,567 --> 00:35:54,527
- Oh, really?
- Really. Yeah.

661
00:35:54,610 --> 00:35:57,697
Yeah, I think it was mainly so fun
because of how similar we are.

662
00:35:57,780 --> 00:35:58,948
- Mmm.
- Yeah.

663
00:35:59,031 --> 00:35:59,949
Right.

664
00:36:05,663 --> 00:36:08,082
Didn't Mina Sue's face
look like that a minute ago?

665
00:36:08,166 --> 00:36:09,250
This is funny.

666
00:36:09,333 --> 00:36:11,127
- She's frozen.
- This is fun.

667
00:36:11,210 --> 00:36:14,046
In terms of what's changed
since this Paradise trip,

668
00:36:14,130 --> 00:36:16,465
a fire has been lit in Mina Sue's heart.

669
00:36:16,549 --> 00:36:19,844
- She's much more desperate for Sung-hun.
- Mmm. Yeah.

670
00:36:19,927 --> 00:36:21,846
I think that's what's changed.

671
00:36:21,929 --> 00:36:24,432
It's Mina Sue's turn
to experience heartache.

672
00:36:25,600 --> 00:36:27,602
Oh, that scared me.

673
00:36:27,685 --> 00:36:29,437
- I hate this.
- I wish this would stop.

674
00:36:29,520 --> 00:36:34,692
<i>Today, there is a guys' game</i>
<i>taking place to win a date to Paradise.</i>

675
00:36:38,779 --> 00:36:40,406
- Oh.
- It's a guys' game.

676
00:36:40,489 --> 00:36:42,074
Here we go.

677
00:36:42,158 --> 00:36:45,244
- I'd like to see them fight this time.
- You keep saying that.

678
00:36:45,953 --> 00:36:47,663
I mean, it's true.

679
00:36:47,747 --> 00:36:50,708
I want to see a bit of a brawl,
if I'm being honest with you.

680
00:36:51,584 --> 00:36:54,170
<i>Please gather at the challenge zone.</i>

681
00:36:55,004 --> 00:36:55,922
Here we go.

682
00:36:56,005 --> 00:36:57,840
Let's not get hurt, guys.

683
00:37:00,843 --> 00:37:03,221
- I-geon's a bit scary today.
- He is.

684
00:37:03,304 --> 00:37:05,389
Wow. I think he'll be
up for revenge today.

685
00:37:05,473 --> 00:37:07,058
Come on, let's go.

686
00:37:21,322 --> 00:37:22,657
What are those lines?

687
00:37:23,532 --> 00:37:25,952
- Maybe it's tug of war.
- I wonder who'll win.

688
00:37:28,621 --> 00:37:31,832
- I-geon's got bangs going on.
- He looks good with bangs.

689
00:37:31,916 --> 00:37:33,542
- Right?
- Yeah.

690
00:37:33,626 --> 00:37:36,837
- Something's in the center.
- Could it be long jump?

691
00:37:43,135 --> 00:37:46,222
<i>Today, the guys</i>
<i>will be competing against each other</i>

692
00:37:46,305 --> 00:37:47,723
<i>to win a date to Paradise.</i>

693
00:37:48,683 --> 00:37:53,437
<i>At the end of the game,</i>
<i>the top three guys, in order of placement,</i>

694
00:37:53,521 --> 00:37:57,024
<i>will each get to pick a girl</i>
<i>to take with them to Paradise.</i>

695
00:37:57,608 --> 00:37:58,943
Same as usual.

696
00:37:59,026 --> 00:38:01,988
<i>I will now reveal today's game.</i>

697
00:38:02,071 --> 00:38:04,448
<i>Please open the box by the trench.</i>

698
00:38:05,533 --> 00:38:06,742
What is it?

699
00:38:07,243 --> 00:38:08,327
What's this?

700
00:38:08,411 --> 00:38:10,079
- Ropes?
- They're not balls.

701
00:38:10,663 --> 00:38:11,914
Oh, no way.

702
00:38:12,832 --> 00:38:15,084
- It's tug of war.
- Oh.

703
00:38:15,167 --> 00:38:18,212
<i>Today's game is Trench Tug of War.</i>

704
00:38:18,296 --> 00:38:20,589
Do they pull each other into the water?

705
00:38:20,673 --> 00:38:23,676
<i>The guys will wear harnesses</i>
<i>connected by a rope</i>

706
00:38:23,759 --> 00:38:26,595
<i>and take their places</i>
<i>on opposite ends of the trench,</i>

707
00:38:26,679 --> 00:38:28,431
<i>where they will begin the battle.</i>

708
00:38:28,514 --> 00:38:30,641
<i>Once the signal sounds,</i>

709
00:38:30,725 --> 00:38:34,437
<i>the person who successfully</i>
<i>drags his opponent into the trench</i>

710
00:38:34,520 --> 00:38:36,022
<i>will win the game.</i>

711
00:38:36,731 --> 00:38:40,359
<i>If there is no winner</i>
<i>at the end of the one-minute time limit,</i>

712
00:38:40,443 --> 00:38:44,864
<i>the person who is furthest from the water</i>
<i>will be the one who wins.</i>

713
00:38:45,948 --> 00:38:49,118
<i>The game is structured like a tournament.</i>

714
00:38:49,201 --> 00:38:52,121
Okay, so basically what it means is,
if they move forward,

715
00:38:52,204 --> 00:38:53,831
the person behind them falls in.

716
00:38:54,582 --> 00:38:55,916
That's crazy.

717
00:38:56,876 --> 00:38:59,295
We've had something similar,
but they didn't fall in the water.

718
00:38:59,378 --> 00:39:01,422
- That's true.
- Now, if they lose it, they fall right in.

719
00:39:01,505 --> 00:39:04,425
They'll fall backwards
into the water like this.

720
00:39:04,508 --> 00:39:05,926
- Like splat!
- Wow.

721
00:39:06,010 --> 00:39:08,554
That's the worst thing that could happen
in front of a girl you like.

722
00:39:08,637 --> 00:39:10,723
- You're totally right, that's awful.
- Too cruel.

723
00:39:10,806 --> 00:39:13,851
Given that this is the last
Paradise trip of the season,

724
00:39:13,934 --> 00:39:17,563
