949
00:54:06,284 --> 00:54:09,913
<i>Three, two, one.</i>

950
00:54:20,298 --> 00:54:21,466
You know, I-geon--

951
00:54:21,549 --> 00:54:23,969
I didn't think
his legs would be so strong.

952
00:54:24,636 --> 00:54:27,055
- His lower body's solid.
- Yeah.

953
00:54:34,354 --> 00:54:36,189
Oh, that rope is so tight.

954
00:54:37,941 --> 00:54:41,361
- They're holding on.
- Hold it, hold it, hold it.

955
00:54:42,404 --> 00:54:44,698
If I-geon just keeps that up, he'll win.

956
00:54:44,781 --> 00:54:46,199
Yeah, just keep holding.

957
00:54:46,283 --> 00:54:48,493
<i>Thirty seconds remaining.</i>

958
00:54:57,752 --> 00:55:00,005
- I-geon's face is about to explode.
- Is he moving?

959
00:55:00,088 --> 00:55:03,300
- He's the type to put it all on the line.
- Yeah, he really is.

960
00:55:06,636 --> 00:55:09,264
This is bad.

961
00:55:16,813 --> 00:55:19,733
- I-geon's so strong. I think he's got it.
- Yeah.

962
00:55:19,816 --> 00:55:21,318
I-geon really is strong.

963
00:55:24,821 --> 00:55:26,781
<i>Twenty seconds remaining.</i>

964
00:55:26,865 --> 00:55:28,575
His face is about to explode.

965
00:55:28,658 --> 00:55:30,869
Some people just have this grit.

966
00:55:30,952 --> 00:55:32,954
Proving he's the game changer.

967
00:55:33,538 --> 00:55:37,083
Yeah, exactly,
by beating the strongest guy here.

968
00:55:38,251 --> 00:55:41,296
I was thinking,
"Is I-geon really trying this hard

969
00:55:41,379 --> 00:55:44,174
because he feels like he has to win
so he can take me to Paradise

970
00:55:44,257 --> 00:55:45,967
and not lose me to Hyeon-woo?"

971
00:55:46,051 --> 00:55:47,469
It caught me off guard.

972
00:55:47,552 --> 00:55:49,888
Have I actually become
that important to him?

973
00:55:50,513 --> 00:55:52,265
The thought made my heart race.

974
00:55:59,105 --> 00:56:01,524
<i>He's banging his head on the ground.</i>

975
00:56:01,608 --> 00:56:04,611
- If he's doing that for you, date him.
- Seriously.

976
00:56:04,694 --> 00:56:07,489
- Isn't that so hot?
- Six months for this amount of effort.

977
00:56:07,572 --> 00:56:09,407
Six months? <i>Unni.</i>

978
00:56:09,908 --> 00:56:12,202
- He's so desperate.
- Yeah, right?

979
00:56:20,835 --> 00:56:24,005
- No, no. Don't get angry.
- Did he get a second wind?

980
00:56:24,089 --> 00:56:26,716
This guy gets a power boost
when he goes into a rage.

981
00:56:33,223 --> 00:56:34,766
Oh, Hyeon-woo.

982
00:56:34,849 --> 00:56:37,060
Hang in there.
You're winning. Hang in there.

983
00:56:40,313 --> 00:56:42,565
Wow, I-geon's holding out really well.

984
00:56:42,649 --> 00:56:45,276
His stamina is unreal.

985
00:56:47,278 --> 00:56:50,490
<i>Ten, nine, eight…</i>

986
00:56:50,573 --> 00:56:52,367
Hyun-jae's insane.

987
00:56:53,993 --> 00:56:55,286
Hyun-jae's insane.

988
00:56:55,787 --> 00:56:58,289
- Oh wow.
- Hyun-jae's insane.

989
00:56:58,373 --> 00:57:00,625
Let's go, Hyun. Let's go, let's go!

990
00:57:01,126 --> 00:57:03,044
Come on,
hang in there just a little longer.

991
00:57:03,128 --> 00:57:05,422
Lock in with your legs.

992
00:57:05,505 --> 00:57:07,298
Hang in there just a little longer.

993
00:57:07,382 --> 00:57:11,136
- Lock in with your legs.
- <i>…four, three, two…</i>

994
00:57:12,011 --> 00:57:13,930
<i>- …three, two…</i>
- So scary.

995
00:57:14,514 --> 00:57:19,018
<i>Ten, nine, eight, seven,</i>

996
00:57:19,102 --> 00:57:25,024
<i>six, five, four, three, two, one.</i>

997
00:57:28,153 --> 00:57:31,197
<i>…three, two, one.</i>

998
00:57:34,534 --> 00:57:37,120
<i>Jo I-geon is the winner of the final.</i>

999
00:57:37,203 --> 00:57:39,289
1ST JO I-GEON, 2ND SHIN HYEON-WOO
3RD YOUN HYUN-JAE

1000
00:57:39,372 --> 00:57:41,875
- He's full of surprises.
- Wow.

1001
00:57:45,128 --> 00:57:46,588
This is cool.

1002
00:57:48,298 --> 00:57:51,092
As they say,
"No one stays on top forever."

1003
00:57:51,176 --> 00:57:54,012
- Oh, I-geon. I-geon's day.
- Wow.

1004
00:58:02,228 --> 00:58:05,190
Wow, I-geon did it.

1005
00:58:05,273 --> 00:58:07,859
What if I-geon falls asleep
as soon as he gets to Paradise?

1006
00:58:08,443 --> 00:58:11,237
- What?
- He's drained his energy.

1007
00:58:11,321 --> 00:58:12,822
He has.

1008
00:58:12,906 --> 00:58:16,201
He arrives, eats, has a quick lie-down,
next minute, it's morning.

1009
00:58:16,284 --> 00:58:18,203
I know, right? He overexerted himself.

1010
00:58:18,286 --> 00:58:21,080
- She'll be like, "Good morning."
- I'm worried about him.

1011
00:58:21,164 --> 00:58:22,749
You're so mean. Seriously.

1012
00:58:22,832 --> 00:58:24,959
- I'm really worried.
- Wow, he's so mean.

1013
00:58:25,043 --> 00:58:26,461
This is the last Paradise trip.

1014
00:58:30,798 --> 00:58:31,883
What?

1015
00:58:31,966 --> 00:58:32,967
I just get the sense that

1016
00:58:33,051 --> 00:58:36,554
Sung-min won't let go of Go-eun
until she's leaving for Paradise.

1017
00:58:37,514 --> 00:58:38,640
- Oh, I agree.
- Seriously.

1018
00:58:38,723 --> 00:58:40,850
I think he'll stay by her side
from this very moment.

1019
00:58:40,934 --> 00:58:42,977
He'll be like,
"Don't change your mind there."

1020
00:58:44,812 --> 00:58:46,356
- Ah.
- So funny.

1021
00:58:47,023 --> 00:58:49,150
Even just watching them was hard.

1022
00:58:49,234 --> 00:58:52,028
- Don't you think?
- I had a really tough time.

1023
00:58:52,111 --> 00:58:54,197
I wonder who I-geon has feelings for.

1024
00:58:54,280 --> 00:58:57,367
I think it's kind of obvious, isn't it?
It's Go-eun.

1025
00:58:57,450 --> 00:59:01,162
He's always trying to talk to her,
and you can tell he wants her attention.

1026
00:59:01,246 --> 00:59:04,624
He wouldn't have gone that far otherwise.
His mind was set.

1027
00:59:04,707 --> 00:59:08,127
- Especially given that his opponent was…
- Him.

1028
00:59:08,211 --> 00:59:10,964
- Hyeon-woo?
- I had no idea he would beat Hyeon-woo.

1029
00:59:11,047 --> 00:59:12,799
What are you thinking, Go-eun?

1030
00:59:13,800 --> 00:59:15,802
Right now, I like them all equally.

1031
00:59:16,719 --> 00:59:18,638
Today's trip is going to be important.

1032
00:59:18,721 --> 00:59:22,475
- Hyeon-woo's in a bit of a tough spot now.
- I know. Who will he go with?

1033
00:59:22,559 --> 00:59:23,726
I know.

1034
00:59:23,810 --> 00:59:26,563
It will fully depend on what I-geon does.

1035
00:59:35,363 --> 00:59:38,908
<i>Singles, you are now free</i>
<i>to go and mingle with one another.</i>

1036
00:59:38,992 --> 00:59:41,578
What the hell?

1037
00:59:41,661 --> 00:59:43,663
- See you guys later.
- This is hard.

1038
00:59:43,746 --> 00:59:45,748
Look at Sung-min. He's off to the races.

1039
00:59:45,832 --> 00:59:47,292
- Wow.
- You were right.

1040
00:59:47,375 --> 00:59:49,586
- I totally called that.
- Yeah.

1041
00:59:49,669 --> 00:59:52,130
He won't leave her side until she goes.

1042
00:59:53,047 --> 00:59:54,299
What is this?

1043
00:59:54,382 --> 00:59:56,134
We can mingle freely.

1044
00:59:57,885 --> 01:00:00,179
Ha-eun, where's Go-eun?

1045
01:00:00,263 --> 01:00:02,432
- I'm in here.
- Where?

1046
01:00:02,515 --> 01:00:05,226
- Come on over.
- Come on, everyone.

1047
01:00:05,727 --> 01:00:08,313
- The guys you're looking for are all here.
- Come in.

1048
01:00:08,896 --> 01:00:11,733
Hey, could I please speak to Sung-hun?

1049
01:00:11,816 --> 01:00:15,028
- Oh, Mina Sue's…
- Everyone's being so proactive.

1050
01:00:15,945 --> 01:00:17,989
- I'm so stressed out.
- Are you really?

1051
01:00:18,072 --> 01:00:20,700
For the first time since coming here,
I'm really stressed.

1052
01:00:22,744 --> 01:00:24,704
- I'm irritated.
- Are you?

1053
01:00:25,288 --> 01:00:27,832
- Sung-min will take her far away.
- Yeah.

1054
01:00:29,751 --> 01:00:32,003
There. All the way over there.

1055
01:00:32,086 --> 01:00:34,297
As far away as he possibly can.

1056
01:00:37,008 --> 01:00:39,135
What are you thinking about right now?

1057
01:00:40,261 --> 01:00:42,013
I am feeling so uneasy.

1058
01:00:43,056 --> 01:00:44,891
- So uneasy.
- Why?

1059
01:00:44,974 --> 01:00:47,393
Because anything could happen
while you're there.

1060
01:00:48,186 --> 01:00:49,103
Mmm.

1061
01:00:49,187 --> 01:00:52,607
I'm honestly dying to know
what's going through your mind right now.

1062
01:00:53,566 --> 01:00:54,567
- Me?
- Yeah.

1063
01:00:54,651 --> 01:00:56,903
I'm not sure either right now.

1064
01:00:56,986 --> 01:00:59,572
- Right now?
- It's difficult right now.

1065
01:01:00,156 --> 01:01:01,491
You're so unpredictable.

1066
01:01:02,158 --> 01:01:03,368
I can't help it.

1067
01:01:03,451 --> 01:01:06,079
You're all such good people,
and you're all so good to me.

1068
01:01:06,162 --> 01:01:08,456
I'm just trying to find
the person who's best for me,

1069
01:01:08,539 --> 01:01:11,167
- that I click with the most.
- Hmm. You're right.

1070
01:01:13,044 --> 01:01:14,879
So you're being dragged away again.

1071
01:01:16,255 --> 01:01:19,467
- I'm not leaving yet.
- That's what my gut is telling me.

1072
01:01:21,844 --> 01:01:23,513
- You're really uneasy.
- Mmm.

1073
01:01:23,596 --> 01:01:25,682
Well, I'm totally sure how I'm feeling.

1074
01:01:26,265 --> 01:01:27,767
But I'm worried you might change your mind

1075
01:01:27,850 --> 01:01:29,602
or just aren't fully sure
of how you're feeling,

1076
01:01:29,686 --> 01:01:31,437
so of course I'm uneasy.

1077
01:01:32,939 --> 01:01:34,273
Are you worried?

1078
01:01:34,357 --> 01:01:36,484
A bit. Actually, a lot.

1079
01:01:36,984 --> 01:01:39,612
You weren't worried to this extent
when I was going with Hyeon-woo.

1080
01:01:39,696 --> 01:01:41,114
- You weren't like this.
- No.

1081
01:01:41,197 --> 01:01:44,575
Well, I didn't feel this way for you
when you were going with Hyeon-woo.

1082
01:01:45,410 --> 01:01:47,161
But I feel anxious this time.

1083
01:01:47,245 --> 01:01:49,497
Like, very. Yeah.

1084
01:01:49,580 --> 01:01:52,166
I think going with someone twice
is different from going once.

1085
01:01:52,250 --> 01:01:53,376
That's true.

1086
01:01:55,253 --> 01:01:57,588
Maybe I've been too relaxed.

1087
01:01:58,256 --> 01:01:59,382
- You?
- Mmm.

1088
01:01:59,465 --> 01:02:02,677
When you're in Paradise,
don't talk too much.

1089
01:02:03,678 --> 01:02:06,431
Don't say anything.
Just sit there and listen to him.

1090
01:02:07,473 --> 01:02:09,100
- Just listen.
- Mmm.

1091
01:02:13,146 --> 01:02:16,315
- I'm kind of curious about Hyeon-woo.
- Yeah.

1092
01:02:16,899 --> 01:02:20,486
If he'd come in first, I'm sure
he'd be thinking the same thing I am.

1093
01:02:20,570 --> 01:02:22,196
I wonder who he's going
to pick now, though.

1094
01:02:22,280 --> 01:02:24,282
It's kind of hard not to be curious.

1095
01:02:32,707 --> 01:02:35,752
So Hyeon-woo's really
only interested in Go-eun.

1096
01:02:35,835 --> 01:02:39,422
Do you think he's wondering which choice
will inconvenience the others the least?

1097
01:02:39,505 --> 01:02:42,300
Or do you think that he's planning
to go with his second choice,

1098
01:02:42,383 --> 01:02:43,885
even if it potentially is someone

1099
01:02:43,968 --> 01:02:46,471
that he really doesn't have
any interest in at all?

1100
01:02:46,554 --> 01:02:48,598
- I don't get the sense that he does.
- You don't think so?

1101
01:02:48,681 --> 01:02:49,515
No.

1102
01:02:49,599 --> 01:02:51,225
He's devoted to one girl.

1103
01:02:52,018 --> 01:02:53,686
INFERNO

1104
01:02:53,770 --> 01:02:58,399
<i>Contestants, we will now begin</i>
<i>the Paradise-bound couple matching.</i>

1105
01:03:02,987 --> 01:03:06,449
- They're choosing.
- Interested to see what Hyeon-woo does.

1106
01:03:06,532 --> 01:03:07,366
Mmm.

1107
01:03:16,501 --> 01:03:18,169
Today is going to be interesting.

1108
01:03:19,796 --> 01:03:22,423
<i>Let's start with Jo I-geon,</i>
<i>who finished in first.</i>

1109
01:03:22,507 --> 01:03:26,135
<i>Please select the person you'd like</i>
<i>to go on a date with in Paradise.</i>

1110
01:03:28,638 --> 01:03:31,057
<i>From the very beginning,</i>
<i>my only thought was that</i>

1111
01:03:31,140 --> 01:03:33,643
<i>I had to come in first place,</i>
<i>no matter what.</i>

1112
01:03:47,865 --> 01:03:50,076
The person I'd like
to go to Paradise with…

1113
01:03:53,621 --> 01:03:54,831
is Kim Go-eun.

1114
01:03:56,916 --> 01:04:00,920
<i>The girl that Jo I-geon</i>
<i>has selected is Kim Go-eun.</i>

1115
01:04:09,345 --> 01:04:10,763
<i>…Kim Go-eun.</i>

1116
01:04:10,847 --> 01:04:13,182
- Oh wow.
- <i>Jo I-geon and Kim Go-eun,</i>

1117
01:04:13,266 --> 01:04:16,602
<i>- please hold hands and leave for Paradise.</i>
- See you later!

1118
01:04:16,686 --> 01:04:17,812
- Bye!
- What are you gonna do?

1119
01:04:17,895 --> 01:04:19,105
Go and enjoy yourself.

1120
01:04:19,188 --> 01:04:21,107
- Have fun. Bye.
- Have a good trip.

1121
01:04:21,190 --> 01:04:23,067
- You're so popular.
- See you tomorrow.

1122
01:04:23,150 --> 01:04:27,238
I'm not surprised. I saw them
get ice cream, I-geon and Go-eun.

1123
01:04:27,321 --> 01:04:28,656
Mmm.

1124
01:04:29,907 --> 01:04:32,660
Oh, I think something big's
gonna happen between them.

1125
01:04:32,743 --> 01:04:33,661
Don't you think?

1126
01:04:34,245 --> 01:04:36,455
This Paradise trip will seal the deal.

1127
01:04:47,216 --> 01:04:50,136
Maybe it was because
my feelings had changed,

1128
01:04:50,219 --> 01:04:52,972
but for some reason,
leaving for the second Paradise trip

1129
01:04:53,055 --> 01:04:54,974
felt totally different.

1130
01:04:55,057 --> 01:04:58,102
The moment I stepped out of the lodge,
I was weirdly nervous.

1131
01:05:03,441 --> 01:05:05,276
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

1132
01:05:06,903 --> 01:05:07,737
Let's go.

1133
01:05:10,865 --> 01:05:12,491
Right in front of him.

1134
01:05:12,575 --> 01:05:13,910
Don't look, don't look.

1135
01:05:22,084 --> 01:05:24,629
- Wow, they look like newlyweds.
- Yeah.

1136
01:05:24,712 --> 01:05:27,214
- They're both wearing white too.
- Oh yeah.

1137
01:05:28,507 --> 01:05:30,718
- My palms are sweaty.
- Why?

1138
01:05:31,844 --> 01:05:33,262
- Are you nervous?
- I must be.

1139
01:05:34,639 --> 01:05:36,599
Ugh, I'm not really
the type to get nervous.

1140
01:05:36,682 --> 01:05:37,600
Really?

1141
01:05:42,647 --> 01:05:45,733
<i>Next up is Shin Hyeon-woo in second place.</i>

1142
01:05:48,986 --> 01:05:51,030
Who do you think Hyeon-woo will choose?

1143
01:05:51,113 --> 01:05:52,615
- I don't know.
- No one knows?

1144
01:05:52,698 --> 01:05:55,785
I actually think someone totally new.
Ye-jin, Ha-eun.

1145
01:05:55,868 --> 01:05:57,161
Oh, I'm so curious.

1146
01:05:57,787 --> 01:05:59,538
Me too. Who will he pick?

1147
01:05:59,622 --> 01:06:02,333
The only one here
who isn't connected to anyone is Ye-jin.

1148
01:06:02,416 --> 01:06:03,292
Yeah.

1149
01:06:03,876 --> 01:06:05,127
Could it be Mina Sue?

1150
01:06:07,296 --> 01:06:08,631
I'm so curious.

1151
01:06:09,548 --> 01:06:12,218
<i>Shin Hyeon-woo, please select the person</i>

1152
01:06:12,301 --> 01:06:15,137
<i>you would like to go</i>
<i>on a date with in Paradise.</i>

1153
01:06:17,056 --> 01:06:20,768
<i>The person I want to go</i>
<i>to Paradise with is Kim Go-eun.</i>

1154
01:06:20,851 --> 01:06:24,063
But since I-geon won first place
in the tournament,

1155
01:06:24,146 --> 01:06:25,773
I had to think really hard about

1156
01:06:25,856 --> 01:06:28,818
what other girl I would potentially
want to take to Paradise

1157
01:06:28,901 --> 01:06:30,319
<i>if he ended up choosing her.</i>

1158
01:06:32,279 --> 01:06:34,156
<i>Shin Hyeon-woo has selected…</i>

1159
01:06:42,248 --> 01:06:47,211
I am forfeiting my trip to Paradise.

1160
01:06:49,922 --> 01:06:51,382
Huh? Is that allowed?

1161
01:06:51,465 --> 01:06:52,883
- Are they--
- Can he do that?

1162
01:06:52,967 --> 01:06:55,636
- This is a first.
- Yeah, it's the first time.

1163
01:06:57,013 --> 01:06:59,515
<i>Shin Hyeon-woo has selected…</i>

1164
01:06:59,598 --> 01:07:00,433
<i>no one.</i>

1165
01:07:00,516 --> 01:07:01,767
What?

1166
01:07:01,851 --> 01:07:05,813
<i>Shin Hyeon-woo</i>
<i>has forfeited his right to choose.</i>

1167
01:07:05,896 --> 01:07:07,648
- <i>…no one.</i>
- Wow.

1168
01:07:10,609 --> 01:07:12,278
What the f***?

1169
01:07:19,035 --> 01:07:21,370
I didn't realize
we were allowed to not choose.

1170
01:07:21,454 --> 01:07:23,581
I had no idea that was an option.

1171
01:07:24,373 --> 01:07:27,835
<i>I ended up making the decision</i>
<i>to forfeit my trip to Paradise today.</i>

1172
01:07:27,918 --> 01:07:29,628
<i>It wasn't a hard decision.</i>

1173
01:07:29,712 --> 01:07:33,299
Aside from Go-eun, there were
no other girls that interested me.

1174
01:07:33,382 --> 01:07:36,635
I had no second or third choice
and didn't want to go as friends.

1175
01:07:38,179 --> 01:07:39,847
So I decided not to go.

1176
01:07:41,432 --> 01:07:43,893
Aw. There's no Go-eun
even if he stays, though.

1177
01:07:43,976 --> 01:07:46,353
- Exactly.
- Seriously.

1178
01:07:46,437 --> 01:07:50,149
- When Go-eun finds out…
- He must have his heart set on her.

1179
01:07:50,232 --> 01:07:52,651
My arm hairs are standing on end,
every one of them.

1180
01:07:52,735 --> 01:07:54,904
Wow. This is just so crazy.

1181
01:07:55,488 --> 01:07:58,532
- I have so much respect for Hyeon-woo.
- Yeah, a lot of respect.

1182
01:07:58,616 --> 01:08:01,994
- I have to hand it to him for this.
- For real. What a plot twist.

1183
01:08:02,495 --> 01:08:04,997
He's totally head over heels for Go-eun.

1184
01:08:05,873 --> 01:08:06,874
Damn.

1185
01:08:12,046 --> 01:08:15,174
<i>Lastly, Youn Hyun-jae in third place.</i>

1186
01:08:15,758 --> 01:08:17,093
<i>Please select the person</i>

1187
01:08:17,176 --> 01:08:20,805
<i>that you would like to go</i>
<i>on a date with in Paradise today.</i>

1188
01:08:21,972 --> 01:08:24,725
The person I'd like
to go to Paradise with…

1189
01:08:27,228 --> 01:08:28,562
is Lee Joo-young.

1190
01:08:33,400 --> 01:08:34,693
- Of course.
- Yeah.

1191
01:08:34,777 --> 01:08:35,820
Last-ditch effort.

1192
01:08:35,903 --> 01:08:37,988
- He's giving it his best shot.
- Yeah.

1193
01:08:38,572 --> 01:08:39,907
<i>Lee Joo-young.</i>

1194
01:08:40,491 --> 01:08:45,454
<i>Youn Hyun-jae and Lee Joo-young,</i>
<i>please hold hands and leave for Paradise.</i>

1195
01:08:45,538 --> 01:08:48,082
- See you later.
- Have fun.

1196
01:08:48,165 --> 01:08:49,667
<i>Lee Joo-young.</i>

1197
01:09:04,014 --> 01:09:05,224
Hello.

1198
01:09:10,521 --> 01:09:12,857
I'm sorry about the rain.

1199
01:09:14,650 --> 01:09:16,026
It's too bad.

1200
01:09:16,610 --> 01:09:20,030
- Ugh. Why did it have to rain?
- How-- I know.

1201
01:09:20,739 --> 01:09:22,116
It's raining.

1202
01:09:22,199 --> 01:09:24,535
Why did it have to rain when I won?

1203
01:09:26,829 --> 01:09:31,417
<i>Today's Paradise-bound</i>
<i>couple matching is now officially over.</i>

1204
01:09:36,172 --> 01:09:39,633
I can't believe he forfeited.
We've never had that.

1205
01:09:55,191 --> 01:09:56,817
Hyeon-woo forfeited his choice.

1206
01:10:01,447 --> 01:10:03,949
- Hyeon-woo.
- Apparently he decided not to take anyone.

1207
01:10:04,033 --> 01:10:05,034
He's not coming.

1208
01:10:05,117 --> 01:10:07,453
- Ah.
- Is that allowed?

1209
01:10:08,454 --> 01:10:09,455
It's 'cause of you.

1210
01:10:18,464 --> 01:10:21,842
I was really surprised to hear
that Hyeon-woo forfeited his choice

1211
01:10:21,926 --> 01:10:24,929
even though that was totally
something he would do.

1212
01:10:25,012 --> 01:10:27,014
It completely caught me off guard.

1213
01:10:27,097 --> 01:10:29,266
I didn't see it coming at all,
but it really got me.

1214
01:10:29,350 --> 01:10:30,559
I'm so touched by it.

1215
01:10:31,602 --> 01:10:34,855
Oh, Hyeon-woo, that was so admirable.

1216
01:10:34,939 --> 01:10:36,065
Not at all.

1217
01:10:36,649 --> 01:10:38,859
It wasn't admirable. I'm bitter right now.

1218
01:10:39,652 --> 01:10:40,986
I'm just so bitter.

1219
01:11:03,217 --> 01:11:05,761
Look at her. Her mind is elsewhere.

1220
01:11:05,844 --> 01:11:08,806
With his experience,
I-geon will navigate this successfully.

1221
01:11:08,889 --> 01:11:11,100
He'll navigate it well
until he reaches success.

1222
01:11:12,017 --> 01:11:14,186
PARADISE
JO I-GEON & KIM GO-EUN

1223
01:11:14,270 --> 01:11:15,854
Do you mind if we rest for a bit?

1224
01:11:15,938 --> 01:11:16,772
Sure.

1225
01:11:17,982 --> 01:11:21,902
Oh, wait. That's what I need to do.
There's something I need your help with.

1226
01:11:21,986 --> 01:11:24,655
- What?
- I need to get something out of my nail.

1227
01:11:24,738 --> 01:11:26,699
Oh. Is it sand?

1228
01:11:26,782 --> 01:11:27,700
Yeah, but I…

1229
01:11:28,534 --> 01:11:30,953
I can't really tell
if it's sand or dried blood.

1230
01:11:32,204 --> 01:11:33,872
- See it?
- Mmm.

1231
01:11:34,832 --> 01:11:36,417
- Does it hurt?
- Mmm.

1232
01:11:36,959 --> 01:11:39,044
Is this… Is it sand, do you think?

1233
01:11:41,922 --> 01:11:44,466
- Yeah.
- Just try to take it all out in one go.

1234
01:11:45,050 --> 01:11:47,594
- Wait. Hold on a second.
- You were about to push it in.

1235
01:11:49,680 --> 01:11:50,764
How do I…

1236
01:11:51,640 --> 01:11:53,517
Why do I have to do this?

1237
01:11:56,353 --> 01:11:58,439
Hold on. I have tweezers. Wait here.

1238
01:12:06,238 --> 01:12:07,323
Tell me if it hurts.

1239
01:12:08,157 --> 01:12:08,991
- So, is it sand?
- Mmm.

1240
01:12:09,074 --> 01:12:10,701
What's this black thing, though?

1241
01:12:10,784 --> 01:12:13,537
Hold on. Let me poke it first
to see if I feel anything.

1242
01:12:16,081 --> 01:12:18,959
It hurts too much to take out.
I guess I'll just leave it.

1243
01:12:19,543 --> 01:12:21,754
- All right, good.
- Good?

1244
01:12:23,839 --> 01:12:25,215
What's good about it?

1245
01:12:28,052 --> 01:12:30,095
- So if you hadn't won…
- Yeah?

1246
01:12:30,596 --> 01:12:34,308
…and I came to Paradise with someone else,
who would you have come with?

1247
01:12:36,852 --> 01:12:39,313
I really don't know
because there's literally no one.

1248
01:12:39,897 --> 01:12:43,233
Maybe just Ha-eun?
But Ha-eun likes Jae-jin, so…

1249
01:12:45,361 --> 01:12:47,196
Oh, this is what I was going to say.

1250
01:12:49,573 --> 01:12:54,953
Because we were in a position
where we could find out about each other,

1251
01:12:55,037 --> 01:12:56,789
even though I was denying it to myself,

1252
01:12:56,872 --> 01:13:00,250
I think I was still kind of wondering
how much you actually knew about me.

1253
01:13:00,334 --> 01:13:04,046
Like, what you'd picked up on
and what kind of person you thought I was.

1254
01:13:04,129 --> 01:13:05,089
- Seriously.
- Yeah.

1255
01:13:05,172 --> 01:13:07,966
I thought it was a shame that
we hadn't gotten time together.

1256
01:13:08,050 --> 01:13:10,177
- I agree.
- I think that's actually what was…

1257
01:13:10,260 --> 01:13:12,679
That's partly what was
holding me back at first.

1258
01:13:12,763 --> 01:13:13,764
- Me too.
- Mmm.

1259
01:13:13,847 --> 01:13:16,975
That's what got me confused
about my feelings for you at first,

1260
01:13:17,059 --> 01:13:19,353
because, like,
I just couldn't work you out

1261
01:13:19,436 --> 01:13:21,939
- and didn't know what you thought of me.
- Mmm, exactly.

1262
01:13:22,022 --> 01:13:23,399
- You know what I mean?
- Yeah, I do.

1263
01:13:23,482 --> 01:13:25,025
After our first conversation,

1264
01:13:25,109 --> 01:13:27,361
you know, when we thought
we might have a mutual acquaintance,

1265
01:13:27,444 --> 01:13:30,864
after that conversation,
I thought to myself,

1266
01:13:30,948 --> 01:13:33,325
"Maybe I should have told him

1267
01:13:33,409 --> 01:13:36,412
that we should disregard all that
and just start from scratch."

1268
01:13:43,460 --> 01:13:45,671
You were really impressive
in the game today.

1269
01:13:47,464 --> 01:13:49,883
- I'm now the strongest guy.
- Yeah, you are.

1270
01:13:49,967 --> 01:13:53,011
- I'm the new strongman here.
- Exactly. The strongman, Jo I-geon.

1271
01:13:53,595 --> 01:13:54,930
Did you root for me?

1272
01:13:55,639 --> 01:13:58,100
- No, I didn't. Not at all.
- Why not?

1273
01:13:58,183 --> 01:14:01,186
Because at the time, you wouldn't have
chosen me to go to Paradise with.

1274
01:14:01,979 --> 01:14:03,439
I knew it, so…

1275
01:14:03,522 --> 01:14:05,399
- What?
- I was praying for you to lose.

1276
01:14:05,482 --> 01:14:06,984
- Oh, really?
- Yeah.

1277
01:14:08,110 --> 01:14:09,611
See this, the scratch?

1278
01:14:10,362 --> 01:14:12,489
Did you get it during the game?

1279
01:14:12,573 --> 01:14:15,909
Yeah, I got scratched
by that cat, Hee-sun. Mmm.

1280
01:14:16,577 --> 01:14:19,288
Hee-sun was really impressive.

1281
01:14:19,371 --> 01:14:20,873
Oh, and I wasn't?

1282
01:14:22,833 --> 01:14:24,042
Uh, maybe a little.

1283
01:14:25,586 --> 01:14:26,628
Am I not impressive?

1284
01:14:26,712 --> 01:14:28,589
Hee-sun was just too dominant
in that game.

1285
01:14:28,672 --> 01:14:30,924
Her facial expression and everything
was so cool.

1286
01:14:31,008 --> 01:14:32,301
- Mmm. Hmm.
- Seriously.

1287
01:14:32,384 --> 01:14:34,094
Then why didn't you talk to Hee-sun?

1288
01:14:34,178 --> 01:14:37,389
- I wanted to.
- What's wrong with you?

1289
01:14:38,390 --> 01:14:40,392
Seriously, what's wrong with you?

1290
01:14:40,476 --> 01:14:42,394
Ugh, minus 50 points.

1291
01:14:44,688 --> 01:14:45,772
For real.

1292
01:14:46,356 --> 01:14:47,441
I'm leaving.

1293
01:14:49,485 --> 01:14:51,487
Hey, look who's talking.

1294
01:14:52,488 --> 01:14:54,156
- I can't believe this.
- I'm out of here.

1295
01:14:54,239 --> 01:14:55,407
You're one to talk.

1296
01:14:55,491 --> 01:14:57,451
- I'm leaving. You can have dinner alone.
- Seriously.

1297
01:14:57,534 --> 01:15:00,412
Even today, you were out walking.
You're unbelievable.

1298
01:15:01,955 --> 01:15:03,624
I'm busy. I'm a busy girl.

1299
01:15:03,707 --> 01:15:05,709
You need to ask me on dates
well in advance.

1300
01:15:05,792 --> 01:15:09,588
I couldn't believe it when I saw you
out walking today. Seriously.

1301
01:15:09,671 --> 01:15:11,089
Get some sleep.

1302
01:15:11,173 --> 01:15:14,259
- I would like to sleep. That sounds nice.
- Why aren't you sleeping? Jeez.

1303
01:15:16,678 --> 01:15:18,680
Tomorrow, I'll go out walking with you.

1304
01:15:19,973 --> 01:15:22,184
No, I'm gonna sleep.

1305
01:15:22,768 --> 01:15:24,311
Let's do a lap here.

1306
01:15:24,394 --> 01:15:25,979
- A lap around the pool.
- Seriously?

1307
01:15:27,648 --> 01:15:30,067
- First thing in the morning.
- Okay.

1308
01:15:31,026 --> 01:15:32,486
"Okay?" Really?

1309
01:15:32,569 --> 01:15:33,904
Are you messing with me?

1310
01:15:34,947 --> 01:15:36,865
- Jesus Christ.
- What's with the "okay"?

1311
01:15:38,200 --> 01:15:41,161
We can't do that. It's too early.

1312
01:15:46,583 --> 01:15:48,043
Are you the jealous type?

1313
01:15:51,380 --> 01:15:53,006
- Yeah. Totally.
- Mmm.

1314
01:15:53,090 --> 01:15:54,299
Totally?

1315
01:15:55,717 --> 01:15:57,553
When I like someone a lot,

1316
01:15:59,054 --> 01:16:01,348
I find it hard to control myself.

1317
01:16:01,431 --> 01:16:04,851
- Mmm.
- It kind of scares me, actually.

1318
01:16:05,936 --> 01:16:08,021
'Cause if I can't control my emotions,

1319
01:16:08,105 --> 01:16:10,399
it's hard to control
my actions or my life.

1320
01:16:10,482 --> 01:16:13,610
- Sounds like you fall really hard.
- Yeah.

1321
01:16:13,694 --> 01:16:15,445
I'm kind of a hopeless romantic.

1322
01:16:18,824 --> 01:16:20,242
And you, do you get jealous?

1323
01:16:20,826 --> 01:16:21,743
Yeah, a lot.

1324
01:16:22,369 --> 01:16:23,495
- A lot?
- Mmm.

1325
01:16:24,538 --> 01:16:27,457
- You don't look like the jealous type.
- I know, right?

1326
01:16:27,541 --> 01:16:29,376
- I get that a lot.
- I can see that.

1327
01:16:31,253 --> 01:16:33,213
Is it starting to rain a lot out there?

1328
01:16:33,714 --> 01:16:36,341
Yeah, it's really
starting to come down now.

1329
01:16:43,223 --> 01:16:45,225
Can you open that curtain a bit more?

1330
01:16:48,145 --> 01:16:50,355
What? It's already open all the way.

1331
01:16:50,439 --> 01:16:52,983
- Oh, I--
- How am I supposed to open it even more?

1332
01:16:56,236 --> 01:16:57,779
Oh, he's right, he's right.

1333
01:17:01,658 --> 01:17:03,869
- Oh, I--
- How am I supposed to open it even more?

1334
01:17:03,952 --> 01:17:06,788
I just wanted to see
more of the rain falling into the pool.

1335
01:17:09,124 --> 01:17:10,959
I didn't think you'd actually do it.

1336
01:17:14,004 --> 01:17:15,005
- Like this?
- Yeah.

1337
01:17:15,088 --> 01:17:17,758
Oh. That's perfect.

1338
01:17:17,841 --> 01:17:19,676
- It was already open.
- I know.

1339
01:17:19,760 --> 01:17:22,804
I like the way he responded, though.
He still went and did whatever he could.

1340
01:17:22,888 --> 01:17:25,849
- You're right.
- Even though he was complaining. Yeah.

1341
01:17:27,392 --> 01:17:28,894
This is too funny.

1342
01:17:29,394 --> 01:17:32,939
- Can you see the rain from where you are?
- Yeah.

1343
01:17:34,483 --> 01:17:35,609
Mmm.

1344
01:17:45,786 --> 01:17:49,915
- I feel so content right now.
- Yeah.

1345
01:17:50,582 --> 01:17:53,210
I don't think
I'll ever forget this moment.

1346
01:17:55,921 --> 01:17:58,090
- I-geon's definitely charming.
- For sure.

1347
01:17:58,173 --> 01:18:01,677
He doesn't entirely go
in the direction that you want him to,

1348
01:18:02,260 --> 01:18:05,013
but at the same time,
he's got so much going for him.

1349
01:18:05,097 --> 01:18:07,432
He's serious, he's playful.

1350
01:18:07,516 --> 01:18:10,852
- That kind of personality is so appealing.
- This is a matter of chemistry.

1351
01:18:10,936 --> 01:18:15,565
Go-eun and Sung-min are like friends
while she and I-geon feel like a couple.

1352
01:18:15,649 --> 01:18:18,568
I've noticed we always
lean towards I-geon, though.

1353
01:18:18,652 --> 01:18:20,487
I feel like Go-eun likes Sung-min,

1354
01:18:20,570 --> 01:18:23,657
but we panelists keep trying
to push her toward I-geon.

1355
01:18:23,740 --> 01:18:24,991
Seriously, you really think so?

1356
01:18:25,075 --> 01:18:27,160
- Are we the ones who like I-geon?
- Look, honestly speaking,

1357
01:18:27,244 --> 01:18:31,081
Go-eun acts completely different
towards I-geon and Sung-min.

1358
01:18:31,164 --> 01:18:33,750
I personally think
it's really obvious, you know.

1359
01:18:33,834 --> 01:18:37,754
Her energy is noticeably different
depending on who she's spending time with.

1360
01:18:37,838 --> 01:18:42,384
Even when, like, I-geon jokes around
with her, Go-eun takes it really well.

1361
01:18:42,467 --> 01:18:44,052
So, yeah, they're so fun to watch,

1362
01:18:44,136 --> 01:18:47,222
and they totally seem like
a couple already to me.

1363
01:18:58,275 --> 01:19:01,486
Who did you come here with last time?

1364
01:19:03,113 --> 01:19:05,490
- Let's just stick to pleasant topics.
- No, I'm just curious.

1365
01:19:05,574 --> 01:19:07,909
- It was with Sung-min.
- Oh, that asshole?

1366
01:19:15,333 --> 01:19:17,836
- It's fine, he's older.
- My gosh, that's so hot.

1367
01:19:17,919 --> 01:19:21,339
At first, I was a bit iffy about this,
but this is just the way he speaks.

1368
01:19:21,423 --> 01:19:23,675
- It's grown on me by now.
- Yeah, it's so refreshing.

1369
01:19:23,759 --> 01:19:24,760
It is refreshing.

1370
01:19:34,561 --> 01:19:36,688
- Is it cold?
- No, it's fine.

1371
01:19:40,817 --> 01:19:42,486
It is a bit cold, actually.

1372
01:19:46,907 --> 01:19:48,909
The water looks pretty clear, though.

1373
01:19:55,874 --> 01:19:57,083
Can you swim?

1374
01:19:58,960 --> 01:20:01,546
- I learned to swim in elementary school.
- Oh.

1375
01:20:01,630 --> 01:20:04,132
When I went in the water,
my body just knew what to do.

1376
01:20:04,216 --> 01:20:05,091
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

1377
01:20:05,675 --> 01:20:07,302
I'm not a good swimmer.

1378
01:20:07,844 --> 01:20:11,181
- Do you know how?
- This is about as much as I can do.

1379
01:20:13,058 --> 01:20:14,142
I'm not very good.

1380
01:20:16,269 --> 01:20:17,562
- Shall I teach you?
- Okay.

1381
01:20:17,646 --> 01:20:18,730
You'll get it in no time.

1382
01:20:18,814 --> 01:20:19,815
Give me your hands.

1383
01:20:21,483 --> 01:20:22,734
Lift your legs.

1384
01:20:22,818 --> 01:20:24,402
- My legs--
- Tense your arms.

1385
01:20:24,486 --> 01:20:25,821
Wait. Stand up.

1386
01:20:25,904 --> 01:20:29,574
- Really? I'm supposed to tense my arms?
- That's what you have to do at first.

1387
01:20:30,283 --> 01:20:31,618
No.

1388
01:20:31,701 --> 01:20:32,911
Is this right?

1389
01:20:34,037 --> 01:20:36,498
- I--
- Can't you put some more muscle into it?

1390
01:20:38,250 --> 01:20:40,252
Your body has to be
a straight line, like this.

1391
01:20:47,092 --> 01:20:48,718
You're not so great either.

1392
01:20:51,805 --> 01:20:53,431
My muscles aren't strong enough.

1393
01:20:54,224 --> 01:20:55,851
And my legs won't float.

1394
01:21:01,314 --> 01:21:02,399
This is funny.

1395
01:21:08,071 --> 01:21:10,282
Do you usually care about height in girls?

1396
01:21:10,365 --> 01:21:11,491
- Height?
- Yeah.

1397
01:21:11,575 --> 01:21:13,743
- Mmm-mmm. More so proportions.
- Oh.

1398
01:21:13,827 --> 01:21:16,621
But doesn't that usually mean
you care about height?

1399
01:21:16,705 --> 01:21:18,915
No, I don't really care
about height at all.

1400
01:21:20,083 --> 01:21:24,087
Petite girls are kind of like fairies.

1401
01:21:24,713 --> 01:21:26,923
- Mmm.
- And tall girls are like goddesses.

1402
01:21:27,007 --> 01:21:29,301
Oh. Mmm.

1403
01:21:29,384 --> 01:21:30,719
When it comes to guys, though,

1404
01:21:30,802 --> 01:21:33,555
short guys are jerks,
and tall guys are bigger jerks.

1405
01:21:34,139 --> 01:21:35,223
All jerks, except me.

1406
01:21:37,309 --> 01:21:39,728
- Especially Hyeon-woo and Sung-min.
- Why?

1407
01:21:47,068 --> 01:21:47,986
Are you jealous?

1408
01:21:48,862 --> 01:21:50,614
- Hmm?
- Are you jealous of them?

1409
01:21:51,281 --> 01:21:53,241
- Do they bother you?
- Mmm.

1410
01:21:53,325 --> 01:21:54,159
Mmm.

1411
01:21:57,871 --> 01:21:58,872
In the game today,

1412
01:22:00,206 --> 01:22:02,959
I won because I knew I wouldn't
be able to stand the sight of you

1413
01:22:03,043 --> 01:22:05,378
leaving for Paradise with someone else.

1414
01:22:12,761 --> 01:22:14,679
I think that was the biggest factor.

1415
01:22:17,098 --> 01:22:19,601
- Lucky I came with you then.
- Yeah.

1416
01:22:27,734 --> 01:22:29,235
You're good-looking.

1417
01:22:30,987 --> 01:22:32,072
You're pretty.

1418
01:22:35,617 --> 01:22:36,826
Did I embarrass you?

1419
01:22:37,661 --> 01:22:39,412
I was just struck by it again.

1420
01:22:43,667 --> 01:22:46,086
My left side's prettier.
Only look at that side.

1421
01:22:48,588 --> 01:22:52,342
- So every time I move back and forth--
- Yeah, I'll keep turning for you.

1422
01:22:53,510 --> 01:22:55,220
Both sides look the same.

1423
01:22:55,303 --> 01:22:56,513
- Really?
- Yeah.

1424
01:23:11,236 --> 01:23:12,112
Wow.

1425
01:23:12,195 --> 01:23:14,614
That right there,
that's the kind of guy Go-eun likes.

1426
01:23:14,698 --> 01:23:17,617
The way he looks at her is so sweet.

1427
01:23:17,701 --> 01:23:19,285
- He looks ready to pounce.
- What?

1428
01:23:19,369 --> 01:23:21,371
- He's ready to pounce, yeah.
- "To pounce…"

1429
01:23:31,965 --> 01:23:33,299
Mmm.

1430
01:23:34,050 --> 01:23:37,095
You know, your face is cute too.

1431
01:23:37,595 --> 01:23:38,722
Is it?

1432
01:23:40,140 --> 01:23:42,892
- Sometimes you're cute.
- When am I cute?

1433
01:23:44,019 --> 01:23:45,979
Come on, tell me. I want specifics.

1434
01:23:49,816 --> 01:23:51,943
Uh…

1435
01:23:59,367 --> 01:24:01,578
So frustrating.

1436
01:24:06,249 --> 01:24:09,127
It seems like you don't actually
get jealous that often, <i>oppa.</i>

1437
01:24:09,210 --> 01:24:11,713
It's only once in a while,
when I talk to Sung-min.

1438
01:24:11,796 --> 01:24:13,214
Right. Mmm.

1439
01:24:15,800 --> 01:24:16,718
I usually…

1440
01:24:18,928 --> 01:24:21,431
try my best not to show that I'm jealous.

1441
01:24:23,475 --> 01:24:24,809
But for some reason,

1442
01:24:25,435 --> 01:24:28,521
you and Sung-min walking this morning
bugged me so damn much.

1443
01:24:28,605 --> 01:24:29,731
- Oh, really?
- Yeah.

1444
01:24:32,817 --> 01:24:35,320
- It did.
- I didn't know you'd be working out.

1445
01:24:36,821 --> 01:24:38,573
You didn't even say hi to me.

1446
01:24:40,283 --> 01:24:41,117
Didn't I?

1447
01:24:58,009 --> 01:25:00,762
This thing is… It's really hot.

1448
01:25:01,304 --> 01:25:03,139
- What is?
- Your scratch here.

1449
01:25:08,686 --> 01:25:10,271
You must have cats around too.

1450
01:25:12,023 --> 01:25:13,024
Sung-min?

1451
01:25:27,789 --> 01:25:29,207
What are you thinking?

1452
01:25:29,874 --> 01:25:31,292
Should I go to you or not?

1453
01:25:35,922 --> 01:25:37,549
What?

1454
01:25:50,103 --> 01:25:51,312
What are you thinking?

1455
01:25:53,106 --> 01:25:55,441
Will you come to me or not?

1456
01:26:13,001 --> 01:26:14,127
You come to me.

1457
01:26:22,010 --> 01:26:23,219
I'll go around.

1458
01:26:58,379 --> 01:27:00,590
Do you think
the age gap between us is big?

1459
01:27:02,592 --> 01:27:03,426
What?

1460
01:27:04,010 --> 01:27:06,930
Do you feel like
the age gap between us is really big?

1461
01:27:07,764 --> 01:27:08,598
I don't know.

1462
01:27:09,557 --> 01:27:10,475
But if…

1463
01:27:11,601 --> 01:27:13,937
we can't feel it, then does it matter?

1464
01:27:14,020 --> 01:27:14,854
No.

1465
01:27:21,903 --> 01:27:22,820
This is nice.

1466
01:27:26,199 --> 01:27:27,242
Hmm?

1467
01:27:42,924 --> 01:27:43,967
What?

1468
01:27:45,385 --> 01:27:46,886
Why are you smiling?

1469
01:27:50,265 --> 01:27:52,600
- I-- I like you.
- Mmm.

1470
01:27:53,101 --> 01:27:54,185
I think I like you.

1471
01:28:05,822 --> 01:28:09,242
There's no heavy physical contact,
but they're so sexy together.

1472
01:28:09,325 --> 01:28:10,535
Mmm, mmm.

1473
01:28:10,618 --> 01:28:14,372
Personally, I think this was the best
pool scene of the entire season.

1474
01:28:14,455 --> 01:28:16,374
- These two just now.
- Yeah.

1475
01:28:16,457 --> 01:28:19,627
The-- The whole
"Should I go" thingamajig--

1476
01:28:19,711 --> 01:28:22,547
What? "Should I go thingamajig?"
How could you be so--

1477
01:28:22,630 --> 01:28:25,383
- "Should I go to you or not?"
- I couldn't imitate.

1478
01:28:25,466 --> 01:28:26,676
And the pose, the pose.

1479
01:28:26,759 --> 01:28:27,760
He was like that.

1480
01:28:27,844 --> 01:28:30,888
Leaning back like this, going,
"Will you come to me or not?"

1481
01:28:30,972 --> 01:28:32,765
- Wow.
- From opposite sides.

1482
01:28:32,849 --> 01:28:34,267
He looked like a male deity.

1483
01:28:34,350 --> 01:28:37,729
It was like some kind of standoff
between a god and a goddess.

1484
01:28:37,812 --> 01:28:39,230
- I've always taken…
- Mmm.

1485
01:28:39,314 --> 01:28:40,523
…the long way.

1486
01:28:41,691 --> 01:28:43,818
Go-eun's feelings
have shifted toward him a lot.

1487
01:28:43,901 --> 01:28:45,403
Yeah, it's kind of like she feels that

1488
01:28:45,486 --> 01:28:47,989
I-geon is a little too rough
around the edges for her,

1489
01:28:48,072 --> 01:28:49,991
but she can't help being drawn to him.

1490
01:28:50,074 --> 01:28:52,285
With the others,
she feels relaxed and at ease.

1491
01:28:52,368 --> 01:28:54,287
They make her laugh and say sweet things.

1492
01:28:54,370 --> 01:28:55,204
But with I-geon,

1493
01:28:55,288 --> 01:28:57,790
there's this underlying tension
whenever they're together.

1494
01:28:57,874 --> 01:28:58,791
It's complicated.

1495
01:28:58,875 --> 01:29:01,085
And I think that's why
she's intrigued by him.

1496
01:29:01,169 --> 01:29:04,589
- Yeah, there's tension. Right.
- That's why I enjoy watching.

1497
01:29:05,298 --> 01:29:06,549
Enjoying yourself, huh?

1498
01:29:06,632 --> 01:29:09,719
No, I mean,
watching them together makes you go,

1499
01:29:10,511 --> 01:29:11,763
- "Aw."
- "I like you."

1500
01:29:13,222 --> 01:29:15,224
- Want to take a picture?
- Okay.

1501
01:29:18,311 --> 01:29:19,312
Hold on a sec.

1502
01:29:32,283 --> 01:29:33,368
Hold on a sec.

1503
01:29:42,293 --> 01:29:43,920
You're wiggling your eyebrows.

1504
01:29:44,837 --> 01:29:46,130
I did exactly what you did.

1505
01:29:46,214 --> 01:29:47,298
- Really?
- Yeah.

1506
01:29:48,841 --> 01:29:49,842
Oh, jeez.

1507
01:29:51,511 --> 01:29:52,804
I'm taking that one with me.

1508
01:29:52,887 --> 01:29:55,139
I think this one's actually
gonna be really funny.

1509
01:29:58,309 --> 01:29:59,727
I can't wait to see it.

1510
01:30:10,780 --> 01:30:12,782
Wait.

1511
01:30:19,247 --> 01:30:21,332
Is this
what my facial expression is usually like?

1512
01:30:21,416 --> 01:30:22,250
No.

1513
01:30:22,333 --> 01:30:24,335
- Is this what I look like?
- Not at all.

1514
01:30:24,419 --> 01:30:25,837
I look like a fool.

1515
01:30:31,259 --> 01:30:32,176
This is nice.

1516
01:30:35,721 --> 01:30:37,932
So, what age do you want to get married?

1517
01:30:39,225 --> 01:30:40,309
28, 29?

1518
01:30:42,937 --> 01:30:44,689
Huh? That's not far off.

1519
01:30:44,772 --> 01:30:45,690
No.

1520
01:30:46,732 --> 01:30:49,235
- Isn't that two or three years from now?
- Mmm.

1521
01:30:50,486 --> 01:30:52,738
I'm not confident
I can get rich within that time.

1522
01:30:57,368 --> 01:30:58,578
Wow.

1523
01:30:58,661 --> 01:31:01,372
He's moving fast.

1524
01:31:02,039 --> 01:31:04,292
I'm not confident
I can get rich within that time.

1525
01:31:08,171 --> 01:31:09,964
- I could earn--
- I need about five years.

1526
01:31:10,047 --> 01:31:11,424
Well, I can earn money.

1527
01:31:11,924 --> 01:31:13,885
- You don't have to be rich.
- That's good.

1528
01:31:17,597 --> 01:31:19,765
- So, do you like what-ifs?
- Hmm?

1529
01:31:19,849 --> 01:31:22,768
- Sure. Try me.
- Well, if you and I got together,

1530
01:31:22,852 --> 01:31:24,604
what do you think
we'd argue about the most?

1531
01:31:24,687 --> 01:31:28,024
Oh, I think we'll have arguments
now and then over the way you talk.

1532
01:31:28,608 --> 01:31:30,818
- Yeah, we'll argue about that too.
- Yeah.

1533
01:31:31,903 --> 01:31:33,988
- But…
- But I think I'd fix it right away.

1534
01:31:34,530 --> 01:31:37,033
- Mmm.
- Once you told me.

1535
01:31:38,659 --> 01:31:41,746
- This convo is so delicious.
- Yeah.

1536
01:31:41,829 --> 01:31:45,082
These two have already moved on
to talking about next-level stuff.

1537
01:31:45,166 --> 01:31:47,376
- Yeah.
- This is like one last test

1538
01:31:47,460 --> 01:31:49,504
before they allow themselves
to get together.

1539
01:31:49,587 --> 01:31:51,088
- Right?
- I think so.

1540
01:31:51,589 --> 01:31:53,007
I kind of…

1541
01:31:54,383 --> 01:31:57,720
get angry easily,
but then I also forget easily.

1542
01:32:00,306 --> 01:32:01,140
Yeah.

1543
01:32:05,311 --> 01:32:06,145
What?

1544
01:32:06,979 --> 01:32:08,481
Do I sound dumb?

1545
01:32:09,190 --> 01:32:12,276
No, no.
This time, I was thinking you were cute.

1546
01:32:13,736 --> 01:32:14,862
You're not dumb.

1547
01:32:14,946 --> 01:32:17,782
If you ever did something
to make me angry,

1548
01:32:17,865 --> 01:32:22,078
mmm… I'd just keep it to myself
until the following day.

1549
01:32:22,161 --> 01:32:24,664
Then I'd probably forget about it.

1550
01:32:26,123 --> 01:32:27,917
- Are you talking about when we're dating?
- Yeah.

1551
01:32:28,000 --> 01:32:30,378
- If we were to start dating?
- Yeah, as long as…

1552
01:32:30,461 --> 01:32:32,588
As long as it wasn't something serious.

1553
01:32:32,672 --> 01:32:35,883
If we were in a relationship
and you did something to make me angry…

1554
01:32:38,052 --> 01:32:39,470
hug me, and I'd be over it.

1555
01:32:40,137 --> 01:32:41,556
- Really?
- Mmm.

1556
01:32:42,139 --> 01:32:43,641
- I'm easy.
- Mmm.

1557
01:32:59,574 --> 01:33:02,201
Keep this to yourself.
I think they slept in the same bed.

1558
01:33:02,285 --> 01:33:03,411
- Hmm?
- Yeah.

1559
01:33:03,494 --> 01:33:04,996
NEXT EPISODE

1560
01:33:06,914 --> 01:33:07,999
Oh, Seung-il.

1561
01:33:08,082 --> 01:33:10,418
You're the jewel of CMU, I'm telling you.

1562
01:33:13,296 --> 01:33:16,882
What did you talk about with Hee-sun
while you were in Paradise?

1563
01:33:16,966 --> 01:33:18,801
I really want to be
totally honest with you.

1564
01:33:18,884 --> 01:33:21,721
- She's keeping her options open.
- I've got goosebumps.

1565
01:33:22,221 --> 01:33:24,640
Why didn't you choose anyone yesterday?

1566
01:33:24,724 --> 01:33:26,726
I'm not interested in anyone but you.

1567
01:33:26,809 --> 01:33:28,144
I won't change.

1568
01:33:28,227 --> 01:33:30,646
My feelings are going to stay
exactly as they are now.

1569
01:33:30,730 --> 01:33:32,064
No matter what.

1570
01:33:32,148 --> 01:33:34,859
Watching you talk with another guy
made me realize

1571
01:33:34,942 --> 01:33:36,527
I shouldn't give them any kind of opening.

1572
01:33:36,611 --> 01:33:38,696
I think I need
a greater show of affection.

1573
01:33:39,405 --> 01:33:43,242
<i>Contestants,</i>
<i>we will now begin the final decision.</i>

1574
01:33:43,326 --> 01:33:45,620
<i>The person I'd like to leave Inferno with…</i>

1575
01:33:49,540 --> 01:33:52,043
The person I'd like to leave Inferno with…

1576
01:33:52,835 --> 01:33:53,836
What?

1577
01:33:54,879 --> 01:33:56,964
I can't believe
none of us saw this coming.

1578
01:33:57,048 --> 01:33:58,883
I know. This is the first time
we all got it wrong.
